141static int compare_uint16_t(const void *p1, const void *p2) {
142 uint16_t u1 = *((const uint16_t *)p1);
143 uint16_t u2 = *((const uint16_t *)p2);
144 if (u1 < u2) {
145 return -1;
146 } else if (u1 > u2) {
147 return 1;
148 } else {
149 return 0;
150 }
151}
152
153// Per http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5246#section-7.4.1.4, there may not be
154// more than one extension of the same type in a ClientHello or ServerHello.
155// This function does an initial scan over the extensions block to filter those
156// out.
157static bool tls1_check_duplicate_extensions(const CBS *cbs) {
158 // First pass: count the extensions.
159 size_t num_extensions = 0;
160 CBS extensions = *cbs;
161 while (CBS_len(&extensions) > 0) {
162 uint16_t type;
163 CBS extension;
164
165 if (!CBS_get_u16(&extensions, &type) ||
166 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &extension)) {
167 return false;
168 }
169
170 num_extensions++;
171 }
172
173 if (num_extensions == 0) {
174 return true;
175 }
176
177 Array<uint16_t> extension_types;
178 if (!extension_types.Init(num_extensions)) {
179 return false;
180 }
181
182 // Second pass: gather the extension types.
183 extensions = *cbs;
184 for (size_t i = 0; i < extension_types.size(); i++) {
185 CBS extension;
186
187 if (!CBS_get_u16(&extensions, &extension_types[i]) ||
188 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &extension)) {
189 // This should not happen.
190 return false;
191 }
192 }
193 assert(CBS_len(&extensions) == 0);
194
195 // Sort the extensions and make sure there are no duplicates.
196 qsort(extension_types.data(), extension_types.size(), sizeof(uint16_t),
197 compare_uint16_t);
198 for (size_t i = 1; i < num_extensions; i++) {
199 if (extension_types[i - 1] == extension_types[i]) {
200 return false;
201 }
202 }
203
204 return true;
205}

207static bool is_post_quantum_group(uint16_t id) {
208 return id == SSL_CURVE_CECPQ2;
209}

211bool ssl_client_hello_init(const SSL *ssl, SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *out,
212 Span<const uint8_t> body) {
213 OPENSSL_memset(out, 0, sizeof(*out));
214 out->ssl = const_cast<SSL *>(ssl);
215 out->client_hello = body.data();
216 out->client_hello_len = body.size();
217
218 CBS client_hello, random, session_id;
219 CBS_init(&client_hello, out->client_hello, out->client_hello_len);
220 if (!CBS_get_u16(&client_hello, &out->version) ||
221 !CBS_get_bytes(&client_hello, &random, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE) ||
222 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&client_hello, &session_id) ||
223 CBS_len(&session_id) > SSL_MAX_SSL_SESSION_ID_LENGTH) {
224 return false;
225 }
226
227 out->random = CBS_data(&random);
228 out->random_len = CBS_len(&random);
229 out->session_id = CBS_data(&session_id);
230 out->session_id_len = CBS_len(&session_id);
231
232 // Skip past DTLS cookie
233 if (SSL_is_dtls(out->ssl)) {
234 CBS cookie;
235 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&client_hello, &cookie) ||
236 CBS_len(&cookie) > DTLS1_COOKIE_LENGTH) {
237 return false;
238 }
239 }
240
241 CBS cipher_suites, compression_methods;
242 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&client_hello, &cipher_suites) ||
243 CBS_len(&cipher_suites) < 2 || (CBS_len(&cipher_suites) & 1) != 0 ||
244 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&client_hello, &compression_methods) ||
245 CBS_len(&compression_methods) < 1) {
246 return false;
247 }
248
249 out->cipher_suites = CBS_data(&cipher_suites);
250 out->cipher_suites_len = CBS_len(&cipher_suites);
251 out->compression_methods = CBS_data(&compression_methods);
252 out->compression_methods_len = CBS_len(&compression_methods);
253
254 // If the ClientHello ends here then it's valid, but doesn't have any
255 // extensions.
256 if (CBS_len(&client_hello) == 0) {
257 out->extensions = NULL;
258 out->extensions_len = 0;
259 return true;
260 }
261
262 // Extract extensions and check it is valid.
263 CBS extensions;
264 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&client_hello, &extensions) ||
265 !tls1_check_duplicate_extensions(&extensions) ||
266 CBS_len(&client_hello) != 0) {
267 return false;
268 }
269
270 out->extensions = CBS_data(&extensions);
271 out->extensions_len = CBS_len(&extensions);
272
273 return true;
274}
275
276bool ssl_client_hello_get_extension(const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello,
277 CBS *out, uint16_t extension_type) {
278 CBS extensions;
279 CBS_init(&extensions, client_hello->extensions, client_hello->extensions_len);
280 while (CBS_len(&extensions) != 0) {
281 // Decode the next extension.
282 uint16_t type;
283 CBS extension;
284 if (!CBS_get_u16(&extensions, &type) ||
285 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &extension)) {
286 return false;
287 }
288
289 if (type == extension_type) {
290 *out = extension;
291 return true;
292 }
293 }
294
295 return false;
296}

304Span<const uint16_t> tls1_get_grouplist(const SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
305 if (!hs->config->supported_group_list.empty()) {
306 return hs->config->supported_group_list;
307 }
308 return Span<const uint16_t>(kDefaultGroups);
309}

311bool tls1_get_shared_group(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint16_t *out_group_id) {
312 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
313 assert(ssl->server);
314
315 // Clients are not required to send a supported_groups extension. In this
316 // case, the server is free to pick any group it likes. See RFC 4492,
317 // section 4, paragraph 3.
318 //
319 // However, in the interests of compatibility, we will skip ECDH if the
320 // client didn't send an extension because we can't be sure that they'll
321 // support our favoured group. Thus we do not special-case an emtpy
322 // |peer_supported_group_list|.
323
324 Span<const uint16_t> groups = tls1_get_grouplist(hs);
325 Span<const uint16_t> pref, supp;
326 if (ssl->options & SSL_OP_CIPHER_SERVER_PREFERENCE) {
327 pref = groups;
328 supp = hs->peer_supported_group_list;
329 } else {
330 pref = hs->peer_supported_group_list;
331 supp = groups;
332 }
333
334 for (uint16_t pref_group : pref) {
335 for (uint16_t supp_group : supp) {
336 if (pref_group == supp_group &&
337 // CECPQ2(b) doesn't fit in the u8-length-prefixed ECPoint field in
338 // TLS 1.2 and below.
339 (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION ||
340 !is_post_quantum_group(pref_group))) {
341 *out_group_id = pref_group;
342 return true;
343 }
344 }
345 }
346
347 return false;
348}

350bool tls1_set_curves(Array<uint16_t> *out_group_ids, Span<const int> curves) {
351 Array<uint16_t> group_ids;
352 if (!group_ids.Init(curves.size())) {
353 return false;
354 }
355
356 for (size_t i = 0; i < curves.size(); i++) {
357 if (!ssl_nid_to_group_id(&group_ids[i], curves[i])) {
358 return false;
359 }
360 }
361
362 *out_group_ids = std::move(group_ids);
363 return true;
364}
365
366bool tls1_set_curves_list(Array<uint16_t> *out_group_ids, const char *curves) {
367 // Count the number of curves in the list.
368 size_t count = 0;
369 const char *ptr = curves, *col;
370 do {
371 col = strchr(ptr, ':');
372 count++;
373 if (col) {
374 ptr = col + 1;
375 }
376 } while (col);
377
378 Array<uint16_t> group_ids;
379 if (!group_ids.Init(count)) {
380 return false;
381 }
382
383 size_t i = 0;
384 ptr = curves;
385 do {
386 col = strchr(ptr, ':');
387 if (!ssl_name_to_group_id(&group_ids[i++], ptr,
388 col ? (size_t)(col - ptr) : strlen(ptr))) {
389 return false;
390 }
391 if (col) {
392 ptr = col + 1;
393 }
394 } while (col);
395
396 assert(i == count);
397 *out_group_ids = std::move(group_ids);
398 return true;
399}

401bool tls1_check_group_id(const SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint16_t group_id) {
402 if (is_post_quantum_group(group_id) &&
403 ssl_protocol_version(hs->ssl) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
404 // CECPQ2(b) requires TLS 1.3.
405 return false;
406 }
407
408 for (uint16_t supported : tls1_get_grouplist(hs)) {
409 if (supported == group_id) {
410 return true;
411 }
412 }
413
414 return false;
415}

469bool tls12_add_verify_sigalgs(const SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
470 for (uint16_t sigalg : tls12_get_verify_sigalgs(hs)) {
471 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, sigalg)) {
472 return false;
473 }
474 }
475 return true;
476}

478bool tls12_check_peer_sigalg(const SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
479 uint16_t sigalg) {
480 for (uint16_t verify_sigalg : tls12_get_verify_sigalgs(hs)) {
481 if (verify_sigalg == sigalg) {
482 return true;
483 }
484 }
485
486 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_SIGNATURE_TYPE);
487 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
488 return false;
489}

491// tls_extension represents a TLS extension that is handled internally. The
492// |init| function is called for each handshake, before any other functions of
493// the extension. Then the add and parse callbacks are called as needed.
494//
495// The parse callbacks receive a |CBS| that contains the contents of the
496// extension (i.e. not including the type and length bytes). If an extension is
497// not received then the parse callbacks will be called with a NULL CBS so that
498// they can do any processing needed to handle the absence of an extension.
499//
500// The add callbacks receive a |CBB| to which the extension can be appended but
501// the function is responsible for appending the type and length bytes too.
502//
503// All callbacks return true for success and false for error. If a parse
504// function returns zero then a fatal alert with value |*out_alert| will be
505// sent. If |*out_alert| isn't set, then a |decode_error| alert will be sent.
506struct tls_extension {
507 uint16_t value;
508 void (*init)(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs);
509
510 bool (*add_clienthello)(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out);
511 bool (*parse_serverhello)(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
512 CBS *contents);
513
514 bool (*parse_clienthello)(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
515 CBS *contents);
516 bool (*add_serverhello)(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out);
517};
518
519static bool forbid_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
520 CBS *contents) {
521 if (contents != NULL) {
522 // Servers MUST NOT send this extension.
523 *out_alert = SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION;
524 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
525 return false;
526 }
527
528 return true;
529}

531static bool ignore_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,

533 // This extension from the client is handled elsewhere.
534 return true;
535}

537static bool dont_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
538 return true;

541// Server name indication (SNI).
542//
543// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6066#section-3.
544
545static bool ext_sni_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
546 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
547 if (ssl->hostname == nullptr) {
548 return true;
549 }
550
551 CBB contents, server_name_list, name;
552 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_server_name) ||
553 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
554 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &server_name_list) ||
555 !CBB_add_u8(&server_name_list, TLSEXT_NAMETYPE_host_name) ||
556 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&server_name_list, &name) ||
557 !CBB_add_bytes(&name, (const uint8_t *)ssl->hostname.get(),
558 strlen(ssl->hostname.get())) ||
559 !CBB_flush(out)) {
560 return false;
561 }
562
563 return true;
564}
565
566static bool ext_sni_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
567 CBS *contents) {
568 // The server may acknowledge SNI with an empty extension. We check the syntax
569 // but otherwise ignore this signal.
570 return contents == NULL || CBS_len(contents) == 0;
571}

573static bool ext_sni_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
574 CBS *contents) {
575 // SNI has already been parsed earlier in the handshake. See |extract_sni|.
576 return true;
577}

579static bool ext_sni_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
580 if (hs->ssl->s3->session_reused ||
581 !hs->should_ack_sni) {
582 return true;
583 }
584
585 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_server_name) ||
586 !CBB_add_u16(out, 0 /* length */)) {
587 return false;
588 }
589
590 return true;
591}

594// Encrypted ClientHello (ECH)
595//
596// https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-tls-esni-09
597
598// random_size returns a random value between |min| and |max|, inclusive.
599static size_t random_size(size_t min, size_t max) {
600 assert(min < max);
601 size_t value;
602 RAND_bytes(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t *>(&value), sizeof(value));
603 return value % (max - min + 1) + min;
604}
605
606static bool ext_ech_add_clienthello_grease(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
607 // If we are responding to the server's HelloRetryRequest, we repeat the bytes
608 // of the first ECH GREASE extension.
609 if (hs->ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request) {
610 CBB ech_body;
611 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello) ||
612 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &ech_body) ||
613 !CBB_add_bytes(&ech_body, hs->ech_grease.data(),
614 hs->ech_grease.size()) ||
615 !CBB_flush(out)) {
616 return false;
617 }
618 return true;
619 }
620
621 const uint16_t kdf_id = EVP_HPKE_HKDF_SHA256;
622 const uint16_t aead_id = EVP_has_aes_hardware() ? EVP_HPKE_AES_128_GCM
623 : EVP_HPKE_CHACHA20_POLY1305;
624 constexpr size_t kAEADOverhead = 16; // Both AEADs have a 16-byte tag.
625 uint8_t ech_config_id;
626 RAND_bytes(&ech_config_id, 1);
627
628 uint8_t ech_enc[X25519_PUBLIC_VALUE_LEN];
629 uint8_t private_key_unused[X25519_PRIVATE_KEY_LEN];
630 X25519_keypair(ech_enc, private_key_unused);
631
632 // To determine a plausible length for the payload, we first estimate the size
633 // of a typical EncodedClientHelloInner, with an expected use of
634 // outer_extensions. To limit the size, we only consider initial ClientHellos
635 // that do not offer resumption.
636 //
637 // Field/Extension Size
638 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------
639 // version 2
640 // random 32
641 // legacy_session_id 1
642 // - Has a U8 length prefix, but body is
643 // always empty string in inner CH.
644 // cipher_suites 2 (length prefix)
645 // - Only includes TLS 1.3 ciphers (3). 6
646 // - Maybe also include a GREASE suite. 2
647 // legacy_compression_methods 2 (length prefix)
648 // - Always has "null" compression method. 1
649 // extensions: 2 (length prefix)
650 // - encrypted_client_hello (empty). 4 (id + length prefix)
651 // - supported_versions. 4 (id + length prefix)
652 // - U8 length prefix 1
653 // - U16 protocol version (TLS 1.3) 2
654 // - outer_extensions. 4 (id + length prefix)
655 // - U8 length prefix 1
656 // - N extension IDs (2 bytes each):
657 // - key_share 2
658 // - sigalgs 2
659 // - sct 2
660 // - alpn 2
661 // - supported_groups. 2
662 // - status_request. 2
663 // - psk_key_exchange_modes. 2
664 // - compress_certificate. 2
665 //
666 // The server_name extension has an overhead of 9 bytes, plus up to an
667 // estimated 100 bytes of hostname. Rounding up to a multiple of 32 yields a
668 // range of 96 to 192. Note that this estimate does not fully capture
669 // optional extensions like GREASE, but the rounding gives some leeway.
670
671 uint8_t payload[kAEADOverhead + 192];
672 const size_t payload_len =
673 kAEADOverhead + 32 * random_size(96 / 32, 192 / 32);
674 assert(payload_len <= sizeof(payload));
675 RAND_bytes(payload, payload_len);
676
677 // Inside the TLS extension contents, write a serialized ClientEncryptedCH.
678 CBB ech_body, enc_cbb, payload_cbb;
679 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_encrypted_client_hello) ||
680 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &ech_body) ||
681 !CBB_add_u16(&ech_body, kdf_id) || //
682 !CBB_add_u16(&ech_body, aead_id) ||
683 !CBB_add_u8(&ech_body, ech_config_id) ||
684 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_body, &enc_cbb) ||
685 !CBB_add_bytes(&enc_cbb, ech_enc, OPENSSL_ARRAY_SIZE(ech_enc)) ||
686 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&ech_body, &payload_cbb) ||
687 !CBB_add_bytes(&payload_cbb, payload, payload_len) || //
688 !CBB_flush(&ech_body)) {
689 return false;
690 }
691 // Save the bytes of the newly-generated extension in case the server sends
692 // a HelloRetryRequest.
693 if (!hs->ech_grease.CopyFrom(
694 MakeConstSpan(CBB_data(&ech_body), CBB_len(&ech_body)))) {
695 return false;
696 }
697 return CBB_flush(out);
698}

711static bool ext_ech_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
712 CBS *contents) {
713 if (contents == NULL) {
714 return true;
715 }
716
717 // If the client only sent GREASE, we must check the extension syntactically.
718 CBS ech_configs;
719 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &ech_configs) ||
720 CBS_len(&ech_configs) == 0 || //

733 }
734 }

795// Renegotiation indication.
796//
797// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5746
798
799static bool ext_ri_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
800 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
801 // Renegotiation indication is not necessary in TLS 1.3.
802 if (hs->min_version >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
803 return true;
804 }
805
806 assert(ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete ==
807 (ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len != 0));
808
809 CBB contents, prev_finished;
810 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_renegotiate) ||
811 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
812 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&contents, &prev_finished) ||
813 !CBB_add_bytes(&prev_finished, ssl->s3->previous_client_finished,
814 ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len) ||
815 !CBB_flush(out)) {
816 return false;
817 }
818
819 return true;
820}
821
822static bool ext_ri_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
823 CBS *contents) {
824 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
825 if (contents != NULL && ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
826 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
827 return false;
828 }
829
830 // Servers may not switch between omitting the extension and supporting it.
831 // See RFC 5746, sections 3.5 and 4.2.
832 if (ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete &&
833 (contents != NULL) != ssl->s3->send_connection_binding) {
834 *out_alert = SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE;
835 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RENEGOTIATION_MISMATCH);
836 return false;
837 }
838
839 if (contents == NULL) {
840 // Strictly speaking, if we want to avoid an attack we should *always* see
841 // RI even on initial ServerHello because the client doesn't see any
842 // renegotiation during an attack. However this would mean we could not
843 // connect to any server which doesn't support RI.
844 //
845 // OpenSSL has |SSL_OP_LEGACY_SERVER_CONNECT| to control this, but in
846 // practical terms every client sets it so it's just assumed here.
847 return true;
848 }
849
850 const size_t expected_len = ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len +
851 ssl->s3->previous_server_finished_len;
852
853 // Check for logic errors
854 assert(!expected_len || ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len);
855 assert(!expected_len || ssl->s3->previous_server_finished_len);
856 assert(ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete ==
857 (ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len != 0));
858 assert(ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete ==
859 (ssl->s3->previous_server_finished_len != 0));
860
861 // Parse out the extension contents.
862 CBS renegotiated_connection;
863 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &renegotiated_connection) ||
864 CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
865 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RENEGOTIATION_ENCODING_ERR);
866 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
867 return false;
868 }
869
870 // Check that the extension matches.
871 if (CBS_len(&renegotiated_connection) != expected_len) {
872 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RENEGOTIATION_MISMATCH);
873 *out_alert = SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE;
874 return false;
875 }
876
877 const uint8_t *d = CBS_data(&renegotiated_connection);
878 bool ok = CRYPTO_memcmp(d, ssl->s3->previous_client_finished,
879 ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len) == 0;
880#if defined(BORINGSSL_UNSAFE_FUZZER_MODE)
881 ok = true;
882#endif
883 if (!ok) {
884 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RENEGOTIATION_MISMATCH);
885 *out_alert = SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE;
886 return false;
887 }
888 d += ssl->s3->previous_client_finished_len;
889
890 ok = CRYPTO_memcmp(d, ssl->s3->previous_server_finished,
891 ssl->s3->previous_server_finished_len) == 0;
892#if defined(BORINGSSL_UNSAFE_FUZZER_MODE)
893 ok = true;
894#endif
895 if (!ok) {
896 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RENEGOTIATION_MISMATCH);
897 *out_alert = SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE;
898 return false;
899 }
900 ssl->s3->send_connection_binding = true;
901
902 return true;
903}
904
905static bool ext_ri_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
906 CBS *contents) {
907 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
908 // Renegotiation isn't supported as a server so this function should never be
909 // called after the initial handshake.
910 assert(!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete);
911
912 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
913 return true;
914 }
915
916 if (contents == NULL) {
917 return true;
918 }
919
920 CBS renegotiated_connection;
921 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &renegotiated_connection) ||
922 CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
923 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RENEGOTIATION_ENCODING_ERR);
924 return false;
925 }
926
927 // Check that the extension matches. We do not support renegotiation as a
928 // server, so this must be empty.
929 if (CBS_len(&renegotiated_connection) != 0) {
930 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_RENEGOTIATION_MISMATCH);
931 *out_alert = SSL_AD_HANDSHAKE_FAILURE;
932 return false;
933 }
934
935 ssl->s3->send_connection_binding = true;
936
937 return true;
938}

1035// Session tickets.
1036//
1037// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5077
1038
1039static bool ext_ticket_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1040 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1041 // TLS 1.3 uses a different ticket extension.
1042 if (hs->min_version >= TLS1_3_VERSION ||
1043 SSL_get_options(ssl) & SSL_OP_NO_TICKET) {
1044 return true;
1045 }
1046
1047 Span<const uint8_t> ticket;
1048
1049 // Renegotiation does not participate in session resumption. However, still
1050 // advertise the extension to avoid potentially breaking servers which carry
1051 // over the state from the previous handshake, such as OpenSSL servers
1052 // without upstream's 3c3f0259238594d77264a78944d409f2127642c4.
1053 if (!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete &&
1054 ssl->session != nullptr &&
1055 !ssl->session->ticket.empty() &&
1056 // Don't send TLS 1.3 session tickets in the ticket extension.
1057 ssl_session_protocol_version(ssl->session.get()) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1058 ticket = ssl->session->ticket;
1059 }
1060
1061 CBB ticket_cbb;
1062 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_session_ticket) ||
1063 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &ticket_cbb) ||
1064 !CBB_add_bytes(&ticket_cbb, ticket.data(), ticket.size()) ||
1065 !CBB_flush(out)) {
1066 return false;
1067 }
1068
1069 return true;
1070}

1088 if (CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
1089 return false;

1174static bool ext_ocsp_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1175 CBS *contents) {
1176 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1177 if (contents == NULL) {
1178 return true;
1179 }
1180
1181 // TLS 1.3 OCSP responses are included in the Certificate extensions.
1182 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1183 return false;
1184 }
1185
1186 // OCSP stapling is forbidden on non-certificate ciphers.
1187 if (CBS_len(contents) != 0 ||
1188 !ssl_cipher_uses_certificate_auth(hs->new_cipher)) {
1189 return false;
1190 }

1192 // Note this does not check for resumption in TLS 1.2. Sending
1193 // status_request here does not make sense, but OpenSSL does so and the
1194 // specification does not say anything. Tolerate it but ignore it.
1195
1196 hs->certificate_status_expected = true;
1197 return true;

1234// Next protocol negotiation.
1235//
1236// https://htmlpreview.github.io/?https://github.com/agl/technotes/blob/master/nextprotoneg.html
1237
1238static bool ext_npn_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1239 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1240 if (ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete ||
1241 ssl->ctx->next_proto_select_cb == NULL ||
1242 SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
1243 return true;
1244 }
1245
1246 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_next_proto_neg) ||
1247 !CBB_add_u16(out, 0 /* length */)) {
1248 return false;
1249 }
1250
1251 return true;

1253
1254static bool ext_npn_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1255 CBS *contents) {
1256 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1257 if (contents == NULL) {
1258 return true;
1259 }
1260
1261 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1262 return false;
1263 }
1264
1265 // If any of these are false then we should never have sent the NPN
1266 // extension in the ClientHello and thus this function should never have been
1267 // called.
1268 assert(!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete);
1269 assert(!SSL_is_dtls(ssl));
1270 assert(ssl->ctx->next_proto_select_cb != NULL);
1271
1272 if (!ssl->s3->alpn_selected.empty()) {
1273 // NPN and ALPN may not be negotiated in the same connection.
1274 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
1275 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NEGOTIATED_BOTH_NPN_AND_ALPN);
1276 return false;
1277 }
1278
1279 const uint8_t *const orig_contents = CBS_data(contents);
1280 const size_t orig_len = CBS_len(contents);
1281
1282 while (CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
1283 CBS proto;
1284 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &proto) ||
1285 CBS_len(&proto) == 0) {
1286 return false;
1287 }
1288 }
1289
1290 uint8_t *selected;
1291 uint8_t selected_len;
1292 if (ssl->ctx->next_proto_select_cb(
1293 ssl, &selected, &selected_len, orig_contents, orig_len,
1294 ssl->ctx->next_proto_select_cb_arg) != SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_OK ||
1295 !ssl->s3->next_proto_negotiated.CopyFrom(
1296 MakeConstSpan(selected, selected_len))) {
1297 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
1298 return false;
1299 }
1300
1301 hs->next_proto_neg_seen = true;
1302 return true;
1303}
1304
1305static bool ext_npn_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1306 CBS *contents) {
1307 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1308 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1309 return true;
1310 }
1311
1312 if (contents != NULL && CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
1313 return false;
1314 }
1315
1316 if (contents == NULL ||
1317 ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete ||
1318 ssl->ctx->next_protos_advertised_cb == NULL ||
1319 SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
1320 return true;
1321 }
1322
1323 hs->next_proto_neg_seen = true;
1324 return true;
1325}
1326
1327static bool ext_npn_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1328 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1329 // |next_proto_neg_seen| might have been cleared when an ALPN extension was
1330 // parsed.
1331 if (!hs->next_proto_neg_seen) {
1332 return true;
1333 }
1334
1335 const uint8_t *npa;
1336 unsigned npa_len;
1337
1338 if (ssl->ctx->next_protos_advertised_cb(
1339 ssl, &npa, &npa_len, ssl->ctx->next_protos_advertised_cb_arg) !=
1340 SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_OK) {
1341 hs->next_proto_neg_seen = false;
1342 return true;
1343 }
1344
1345 CBB contents;
1346 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_next_proto_neg) ||
1347 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
1348 !CBB_add_bytes(&contents, npa, npa_len) ||
1349 !CBB_flush(out)) {
1350 return false;
1351 }
1352
1353 return true;
1354}

1357// Signed certificate timestamps.

1362 if (!hs->config->signed_cert_timestamps_enabled) {
1363 return true;
1364 }
1365
1366 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_certificate_timestamp) ||

1373
1374static bool ext_sct_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1375 CBS *contents) {
1376 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1377 if (contents == NULL) {
1378 return true;
1379 }
1380
1381 // TLS 1.3 SCTs are included in the Certificate extensions.
1382 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1383 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1384 return false;
1385 }
1386
1387 // If this is false then we should never have sent the SCT extension in the
1388 // ClientHello and thus this function should never have been called.
1389 assert(hs->config->signed_cert_timestamps_enabled);
1390
1391 if (!ssl_is_sct_list_valid(contents)) {
1392 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1393 return false;
1394 }
1395
1396 // Session resumption uses the original session information. The extension
1397 // should not be sent on resumption, but RFC 6962 did not make it a
1398 // requirement, so tolerate this.
1399 //
1400 // TODO(davidben): Enforce this anyway.
1401 if (!ssl->s3->session_reused) {
1402 hs->new_session->signed_cert_timestamp_list.reset(
1403 CRYPTO_BUFFER_new_from_CBS(contents, ssl->ctx->pool));
1404 if (hs->new_session->signed_cert_timestamp_list == nullptr) {
1405 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
1406 return false;
1407 }
1408 }
1409
1410 return true;
1411}
1412
1413static bool ext_sct_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1414 CBS *contents) {
1415 if (contents == NULL) {
1416 return true;
1417 }
1418
1419 if (CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
1420 return false;
1421 }
1422
1423 hs->scts_requested = true;
1424 return true;
1425}

1427static bool ext_sct_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1428 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1429 // The extension shouldn't be sent when resuming sessions.
1430 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION || ssl->s3->session_reused ||
1431 hs->config->cert->signed_cert_timestamp_list == NULL) {
1432 return true;
1433 }
1434
1435 CBB contents;
1436 return CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_certificate_timestamp) &&
1437 CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) &&
1438 CBB_add_bytes(
1439 &contents,
1440 CRYPTO_BUFFER_data(
1441 hs->config->cert->signed_cert_timestamp_list.get()),
1442 CRYPTO_BUFFER_len(
1443 hs->config->cert->signed_cert_timestamp_list.get())) &&
1444 CBB_flush(out);
1445}

1448// Application-level Protocol Negotiation.
1449//
1450// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7301
1451
1452static bool ext_alpn_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1453 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1454 if (hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.empty() && ssl->quic_method) {
1455 // ALPN MUST be used with QUIC.
1456 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_APPLICATION_PROTOCOL);
1457 return false;
1458 }
1459
1460 if (hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.empty() ||
1461 ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete) {
1462 return true;
1463 }
1464
1465 CBB contents, proto_list;
1466 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_application_layer_protocol_negotiation) ||
1467 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
1468 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &proto_list) ||
1469 !CBB_add_bytes(&proto_list, hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.data(),
1470 hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.size()) ||
1471 !CBB_flush(out)) {
1472 return false;
1473 }
1474
1475 return true;
1476}
1477
1478static bool ext_alpn_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1479 CBS *contents) {
1480 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1481 if (contents == NULL) {
1482 if (ssl->quic_method) {
1483 // ALPN is required when QUIC is used.
1484 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_APPLICATION_PROTOCOL);
1485 *out_alert = SSL_AD_NO_APPLICATION_PROTOCOL;
1486 return false;
1487 }
1488 return true;
1489 }
1490
1491 assert(!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete);
1492 assert(!hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.empty());
1493
1494 if (hs->next_proto_neg_seen) {
1495 // NPN and ALPN may not be negotiated in the same connection.
1496 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
1497 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NEGOTIATED_BOTH_NPN_AND_ALPN);
1498 return false;
1499 }
1500
1501 // The extension data consists of a ProtocolNameList which must have
1502 // exactly one ProtocolName. Each of these is length-prefixed.
1503 CBS protocol_name_list, protocol_name;
1504 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &protocol_name_list) ||
1505 CBS_len(contents) != 0 ||
1506 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&protocol_name_list, &protocol_name) ||
1507 // Empty protocol names are forbidden.
1508 CBS_len(&protocol_name) == 0 ||
1509 CBS_len(&protocol_name_list) != 0) {
1510 return false;
1511 }
1512
1513 if (!ssl_is_alpn_protocol_allowed(hs, protocol_name)) {
1514 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_ALPN_PROTOCOL);
1515 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
1516 return false;
1517 }
1518
1519 if (!ssl->s3->alpn_selected.CopyFrom(protocol_name)) {
1520 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
1521 return false;
1522 }
1523
1524 return true;
1525}
1526
1527bool ssl_is_valid_alpn_list(Span<const uint8_t> in) {
1528 CBS protocol_name_list = in;
1529 if (CBS_len(&protocol_name_list) == 0) {
1530 return false;
1531 }
1532 while (CBS_len(&protocol_name_list) > 0) {
1533 CBS protocol_name;
1534 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&protocol_name_list, &protocol_name) ||
1535 // Empty protocol names are forbidden.
1536 CBS_len(&protocol_name) == 0) {
1537 return false;
1538 }
1539 }
1540 return true;
1541}
1542
1543bool ssl_is_alpn_protocol_allowed(const SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
1544 Span<const uint8_t> protocol) {
1545 if (hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.empty()) {
1546 return false;
1547 }
1548
1549 if (hs->ssl->ctx->allow_unknown_alpn_protos) {
1550 return true;
1551 }
1552
1553 // Check that the protocol name is one of the ones we advertised.
1554 CBS client_protocol_name_list =
1555 MakeConstSpan(hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list),
1556 client_protocol_name;
1557 while (CBS_len(&client_protocol_name_list) > 0) {
1558 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&client_protocol_name_list,
1559 &client_protocol_name)) {
1560 return false;
1561 }
1562
1563 if (client_protocol_name == protocol) {
1564 return true;
1565 }
1566 }
1567
1568 return false;
1569}
1570
1571bool ssl_negotiate_alpn(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1572 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
1573 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1574 CBS contents;
1575 if (ssl->ctx->alpn_select_cb == NULL ||
1576 !ssl_client_hello_get_extension(
1577 client_hello, &contents,
1578 TLSEXT_TYPE_application_layer_protocol_negotiation)) {
1579 if (ssl->quic_method) {
1580 // ALPN is required when QUIC is used.
1581 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_APPLICATION_PROTOCOL);
1582 *out_alert = SSL_AD_NO_APPLICATION_PROTOCOL;
1583 return false;
1584 }
1585 // Ignore ALPN if not configured or no extension was supplied.
1586 return true;
1587 }
1588
1589 // ALPN takes precedence over NPN.
1590 hs->next_proto_neg_seen = false;
1591
1592 CBS protocol_name_list;
1593 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &protocol_name_list) ||
1594 CBS_len(&contents) != 0 ||
1595 !ssl_is_valid_alpn_list(protocol_name_list)) {
1596 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PARSE_TLSEXT);
1597 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1598 return false;
1599 }
1600
1601 const uint8_t *selected;
1602 uint8_t selected_len;
1603 int ret = ssl->ctx->alpn_select_cb(
1604 ssl, &selected, &selected_len, CBS_data(&protocol_name_list),
1605 CBS_len(&protocol_name_list), ssl->ctx->alpn_select_cb_arg);
1606 // ALPN is required when QUIC is used.
1607 if (ssl->quic_method &&
1608 (ret == SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_NOACK || ret == SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_ALERT_WARNING)) {
1609 ret = SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_ALERT_FATAL;
1610 }
1611 switch (ret) {
1612 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_OK:
1613 if (selected_len == 0) {
1614 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_ALPN_PROTOCOL);
1615 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
1616 return false;
1617 }
1618 if (!ssl->s3->alpn_selected.CopyFrom(
1619 MakeConstSpan(selected, selected_len))) {
1620 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
1621 return false;
1622 }
1623 break;
1624 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_NOACK:
1625 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_ALERT_WARNING:
1626 break;
1627 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_ALERT_FATAL:
1628 *out_alert = SSL_AD_NO_APPLICATION_PROTOCOL;
1629 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_APPLICATION_PROTOCOL);
1630 return false;
1631 default:
1632 // Invalid return value.
1633 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
1634 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
1635 return false;
1636 }
1637
1638 return true;
1639}

1642 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1643 if (ssl->s3->alpn_selected.empty()) {
1644 return true;
1645 }
1646
1647 CBB contents, proto_list, proto;
1648 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_application_layer_protocol_negotiation) ||

1650 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &proto_list) ||
1651 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&proto_list, &proto) ||
1652 !CBB_add_bytes(&proto, ssl->s3->alpn_selected.data(),

1655 return false;

1734// Secure Real-time Transport Protocol (SRTP) extension.
1735//
1736// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5764
1737
1738
1739static void ext_srtp_init(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1740 hs->ssl->s3->srtp_profile = NULL;
1741}
1742
1743static bool ext_srtp_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1744 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1745 STACK_OF(SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE) *profiles = SSL_get_srtp_profiles(ssl);
1746 if (profiles == NULL ||
1747 sk_SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE_num(profiles) == 0) {
1748 return true;
1749 }
1750
1751 CBB contents, profile_ids;
1752 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_srtp) ||
1753 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
1754 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &profile_ids)) {
1755 return false;
1756 }
1757
1758 for (const SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE *profile : profiles) {
1759 if (!CBB_add_u16(&profile_ids, profile->id)) {
1760 return false;
1761 }
1762 }
1763
1764 if (!CBB_add_u8(&contents, 0 /* empty use_mki value */) ||
1765 !CBB_flush(out)) {
1766 return false;
1767 }
1768
1769 return true;
1770}
1771
1772static bool ext_srtp_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1773 CBS *contents) {
1774 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1775 if (contents == NULL) {
1776 return true;
1777 }
1778
1779 // The extension consists of a u16-prefixed profile ID list containing a
1780 // single uint16_t profile ID, then followed by a u8-prefixed srtp_mki field.
1781 //
1782 // See https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5764#section-4.1.1
1783 CBS profile_ids, srtp_mki;
1784 uint16_t profile_id;
1785 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &profile_ids) ||
1786 !CBS_get_u16(&profile_ids, &profile_id) ||
1787 CBS_len(&profile_ids) != 0 ||
1788 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &srtp_mki) ||
1789 CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
1790 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE_LIST);
1791 return false;
1792 }
1793
1794 if (CBS_len(&srtp_mki) != 0) {
1795 // Must be no MKI, since we never offer one.
1796 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_SRTP_MKI_VALUE);
1797 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
1798 return false;
1799 }
1800
1801 STACK_OF(SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE) *profiles = SSL_get_srtp_profiles(ssl);
1802
1803 // Check to see if the server gave us something we support (and presumably
1804 // offered).
1805 for (const SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE *profile : profiles) {
1806 if (profile->id == profile_id) {
1807 ssl->s3->srtp_profile = profile;
1808 return true;
1809 }
1810 }
1811
1812 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE_LIST);
1813 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
1814 return false;
1815}
1816
1817static bool ext_srtp_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
1818 CBS *contents) {
1819 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1820 if (contents == NULL) {
1821 return true;
1822 }
1823
1824 CBS profile_ids, srtp_mki;
1825 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &profile_ids) ||
1826 CBS_len(&profile_ids) < 2 ||
1827 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &srtp_mki) ||
1828 CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
1829 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_BAD_SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE_LIST);
1830 return false;
1831 }
1832 // Discard the MKI value for now.
1833
1834 const STACK_OF(SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE) *server_profiles =
1835 SSL_get_srtp_profiles(ssl);
1836
1837 // Pick the server's most preferred profile.
1838 for (const SRTP_PROTECTION_PROFILE *server_profile : server_profiles) {
1839 CBS profile_ids_tmp;
1840 CBS_init(&profile_ids_tmp, CBS_data(&profile_ids), CBS_len(&profile_ids));
1841
1842 while (CBS_len(&profile_ids_tmp) > 0) {
1843 uint16_t profile_id;
1844 if (!CBS_get_u16(&profile_ids_tmp, &profile_id)) {
1845 return false;
1846 }
1847
1848 if (server_profile->id == profile_id) {
1849 ssl->s3->srtp_profile = server_profile;
1850 return true;
1851 }
1852 }
1853 }
1854
1855 return true;
1856}
1857
1858static bool ext_srtp_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1859 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1860 if (ssl->s3->srtp_profile == NULL) {
1861 return true;
1862 }
1863
1864 CBB contents, profile_ids;
1865 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_srtp) ||
1866 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
1867 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &profile_ids) ||
1868 !CBB_add_u16(&profile_ids, ssl->s3->srtp_profile->id) ||
1869 !CBB_add_u8(&contents, 0 /* empty MKI */) ||
1870 !CBB_flush(out)) {
1871 return false;
1872 }
1873
1874 return true;
1875}

1904static bool ext_ec_point_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,

1940
1941static bool ext_ec_point_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1942 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1943 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1944 return true;
1945 }
1946
1947 const uint32_t alg_k = hs->new_cipher->algorithm_mkey;
1948 const uint32_t alg_a = hs->new_cipher->algorithm_auth;
1949 const bool using_ecc = (alg_k & SSL_kECDHE) || (alg_a & SSL_aECDSA);
1950
1951 if (!using_ecc) {
1952 return true;
1953 }
1954
1955 return ext_ec_point_add_extension(hs, out);
1956}

1959// Pre Shared Key
1960//
1961// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8446#section-4.2.11
1962
1963static size_t ext_pre_shared_key_clienthello_length(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
1964 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1965 if (hs->max_version < TLS1_3_VERSION || ssl->session == nullptr ||
1966 ssl_session_protocol_version(ssl->session.get()) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1967 return 0;
1968 }
1969
1970 size_t binder_len = EVP_MD_size(ssl_session_get_digest(ssl->session.get()));
1971 return 15 + ssl->session->ticket.size() + binder_len;
1972}
1973
1974static bool ext_pre_shared_key_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
1975 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
1976 hs->needs_psk_binder = false;
1977 if (hs->max_version < TLS1_3_VERSION || ssl->session == nullptr ||
1978 ssl_session_protocol_version(ssl->session.get()) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
1979 return true;
1980 }
1981
1982 // Per RFC 8446 section 4.1.4, skip offering the session if the selected
1983 // cipher in HelloRetryRequest does not match. This avoids performing the
1984 // transcript hash transformation for multiple hashes.
1985 if (ssl->s3 && ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request &&
1986 ssl->session->cipher->algorithm_prf != hs->new_cipher->algorithm_prf) {
1987 return true;
1988 }
1989
1990 struct OPENSSL_timeval now;
1991 ssl_get_current_time(ssl, &now);
1992 uint32_t ticket_age = 1000 * (now.tv_sec - ssl->session->time);
1993 uint32_t obfuscated_ticket_age = ticket_age + ssl->session->ticket_age_add;
1994
1995 // Fill in a placeholder zero binder of the appropriate length. It will be
1996 // computed and filled in later after length prefixes are computed.
1997 uint8_t zero_binder[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE] = {0};
1998 size_t binder_len = EVP_MD_size(ssl_session_get_digest(ssl->session.get()));
1999
2000 CBB contents, identity, ticket, binders, binder;
2001 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_pre_shared_key) ||
2002 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
2003 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &identity) ||
2004 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&identity, &ticket) ||
2005 !CBB_add_bytes(&ticket, ssl->session->ticket.data(),
2006 ssl->session->ticket.size()) ||
2007 !CBB_add_u32(&identity, obfuscated_ticket_age) ||
2008 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &binders) ||
2009 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&binders, &binder) ||
2010 !CBB_add_bytes(&binder, zero_binder, binder_len)) {
2011 return false;
2012 }
2013
2014 hs->needs_psk_binder = true;
2015 return CBB_flush(out);
2016}
2017
2018bool ssl_ext_pre_shared_key_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
2019 uint8_t *out_alert,
2020 CBS *contents) {
2021 uint16_t psk_id;
2022 if (!CBS_get_u16(contents, &psk_id) ||
2023 CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
2024 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2025 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2026 return false;
2027 }
2028
2029 // We only advertise one PSK identity, so the only legal index is zero.
2030 if (psk_id != 0) {
2031 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PSK_IDENTITY_NOT_FOUND);
2032 *out_alert = SSL_AD_UNKNOWN_PSK_IDENTITY;
2033 return false;
2034 }
2035
2036 return true;
2037}
2038
2039bool ssl_ext_pre_shared_key_parse_clienthello(
2040 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBS *out_ticket, CBS *out_binders,
2041 uint32_t *out_obfuscated_ticket_age, uint8_t *out_alert,
2042 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello, CBS *contents) {
2043 // Verify that the pre_shared_key extension is the last extension in
2044 // ClientHello.
2045 if (CBS_data(contents) + CBS_len(contents) !=
2046 client_hello->extensions + client_hello->extensions_len) {
2047 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PRE_SHARED_KEY_MUST_BE_LAST);
2048 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
2049 return false;
2050 }
2051
2052 // We only process the first PSK identity since we don't support pure PSK.
2053 CBS identities, binders;
2054 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &identities) ||
2055 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&identities, out_ticket) ||
2056 !CBS_get_u32(&identities, out_obfuscated_ticket_age) ||
2057 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &binders) ||
2058 CBS_len(&binders) == 0 ||
2059 CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
2060 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2061 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2062 return false;
2063 }
2064
2065 *out_binders = binders;
2066
2067 // Check the syntax of the remaining identities, but do not process them.
2068 size_t num_identities = 1;
2069 while (CBS_len(&identities) != 0) {
2070 CBS unused_ticket;
2071 uint32_t unused_obfuscated_ticket_age;
2072 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&identities, &unused_ticket) ||
2073 !CBS_get_u32(&identities, &unused_obfuscated_ticket_age)) {
2074 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2075 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2076 return false;
2077 }
2078
2079 num_identities++;
2080 }
2081
2082 // Check the syntax of the binders. The value will be checked later if
2083 // resuming.
2084 size_t num_binders = 0;
2085 while (CBS_len(&binders) != 0) {
2086 CBS binder;
2087 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&binders, &binder)) {
2088 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2089 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2090 return false;
2091 }
2092
2093 num_binders++;
2094 }
2095
2096 if (num_identities != num_binders) {
2097 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PSK_IDENTITY_BINDER_COUNT_MISMATCH);
2098 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
2099 return false;
2100 }
2101
2102 return true;
2103}

2106 if (!hs->ssl->s3->session_reused) {
2107 return true;

2109
2110 CBB contents;
2111 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_pre_shared_key) ||

2113 // We only consider the first identity for resumption
2114 !CBB_add_u16(&contents, 0) ||
2115 !CBB_flush(out)) {
2116 return false;
2117 }
2118
2119 return true;
2120}

2186static bool ext_early_data_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
2187 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2188 // The second ClientHello never offers early data, and we must have already
2189 // filled in |early_data_reason| by this point.
2190 if (ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request) {
2191 assert(ssl->s3->early_data_reason != ssl_early_data_unknown);
2192 return true;
2193 }
2194
2195 if (!ssl->enable_early_data) {
2196 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_disabled;
2197 return true;
2198 }
2199
2200 if (hs->max_version < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
2201 // We discard inapplicable sessions, so this is redundant with the session
2202 // checks below, but we check give a more useful reason.
2203 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_protocol_version;
2204 return true;
2205 }
2206
2207 if (ssl->session == nullptr) {
2208 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_no_session_offered;
2209 return true;
2210 }
2211
2212 if (ssl_session_protocol_version(ssl->session.get()) < TLS1_3_VERSION ||
2213 ssl->session->ticket_max_early_data == 0) {
2214 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_unsupported_for_session;
2215 return true;
2216 }
2217
2218 if (!ssl->session->early_alpn.empty()) {
2219 if (!ssl_is_alpn_protocol_allowed(hs, ssl->session->early_alpn)) {
2220 // Avoid reporting a confusing value in |SSL_get0_alpn_selected|.
2221 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_alpn_mismatch;
2222 return true;
2223 }
2224
2225 // If the previous connection negotiated ALPS, only offer 0-RTT when the
2226 // local are settings are consistent with what we'd offer for this
2227 // connection.
2228 if (ssl->session->has_application_settings) {
2229 Span<const uint8_t> settings;
2230 if (!ssl_get_local_application_settings(hs, &settings,
2231 ssl->session->early_alpn) ||
2232 settings != ssl->session->local_application_settings) {
2233 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_alps_mismatch;
2234 return true;
2235 }
2236 }
2237 }
2238
2239 // |early_data_reason| will be filled in later when the server responds.
2240 hs->early_data_offered = true;
2241
2242 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_early_data) ||
2243 !CBB_add_u16(out, 0) ||
2244 !CBB_flush(out)) {
2245 return false;
2246 }
2247
2248 return true;
2249}

2251static bool ext_early_data_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
2252 uint8_t *out_alert,
2253 CBS *contents) {
2254 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2255 if (contents == NULL) {
2256 if (hs->early_data_offered && !ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request) {
2257 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl->s3->session_reused
2258 ? ssl_early_data_peer_declined
2259 : ssl_early_data_session_not_resumed;
2260 } else {
2261 // We already filled in |early_data_reason| when declining to offer 0-RTT
2262 // or handling the implicit HelloRetryRequest reject.
2263 assert(ssl->s3->early_data_reason != ssl_early_data_unknown);
2264 }
2265 return true;
2266 }
2267
2268 // If we received an HRR, the second ClientHello never offers early data, so
2269 // the extensions logic will automatically reject early data extensions as
2270 // unsolicited. This covered by the ServerAcceptsEarlyDataOnHRR test.
2271 assert(!ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request);
2272
2273 if (CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
2274 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2275 return false;
2276 }
2277
2278 if (!ssl->s3->session_reused) {
2279 *out_alert = SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION;
2280 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
2281 return false;
2282 }
2283
2284 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_accepted;
2285 ssl->s3->early_data_accepted = true;
2286 return true;
2287}

2321// Key Share
2322//
2323// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8446#section-4.2.8
2324
2325static bool ext_key_share_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
2326 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2327 if (hs->max_version < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
2328 return true;
2329 }
2330
2331 CBB contents, kse_bytes;
2332 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_key_share) ||
2333 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
2334 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &kse_bytes)) {
2335 return false;
2336 }
2337
2338 uint16_t group_id = hs->retry_group;
2339 uint16_t second_group_id = 0;
2340 if (ssl->s3 && ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request) {
2341 // We received a HelloRetryRequest without a new curve, so there is no new
2342 // share to append. Leave |hs->key_share| as-is.
2343 if (group_id == 0 &&
2344 !CBB_add_bytes(&kse_bytes, hs->key_share_bytes.data(),
2345 hs->key_share_bytes.size())) {
2346 return false;
2347 }
2348 hs->key_share_bytes.Reset();
2349 if (group_id == 0) {
2350 return CBB_flush(out);
2351 }
2352 } else {
2353 // Add a fake group. See draft-davidben-tls-grease-01.
2354 if (ssl->ctx->grease_enabled &&
2355 (!CBB_add_u16(&kse_bytes,
2356 ssl_get_grease_value(hs, ssl_grease_group)) ||
2357 !CBB_add_u16(&kse_bytes, 1 /* length */) ||
2358 !CBB_add_u8(&kse_bytes, 0 /* one byte key share */))) {
2359 return false;
2360 }
2361
2362 // Predict the most preferred group.
2363 Span<const uint16_t> groups = tls1_get_grouplist(hs);
2364 if (groups.empty()) {
2365 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_GROUPS_SPECIFIED);
2366 return false;
2367 }
2368
2369 group_id = groups[0];
2370
2371 if (is_post_quantum_group(group_id) && groups.size() >= 2) {
2372 // CECPQ2(b) is not sent as the only initial key share. We'll include the
2373 // 2nd preference group too to avoid round-trips.
2374 second_group_id = groups[1];
2375 assert(second_group_id != group_id);
2376 }
2377 }
2378
2379 CBB key_exchange;
2380 hs->key_shares[0] = SSLKeyShare::Create(group_id);
2381 if (!hs->key_shares[0] ||
2382 !CBB_add_u16(&kse_bytes, group_id) ||
2383 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&kse_bytes, &key_exchange) ||
2384 !hs->key_shares[0]->Offer(&key_exchange) ||
2385 !CBB_flush(&kse_bytes)) {
2386 return false;
2387 }
2388
2389 if (second_group_id != 0) {
2390 hs->key_shares[1] = SSLKeyShare::Create(second_group_id);
2391 if (!hs->key_shares[1] ||
2392 !CBB_add_u16(&kse_bytes, second_group_id) ||
2393 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&kse_bytes, &key_exchange) ||
2394 !hs->key_shares[1]->Offer(&key_exchange) ||
2395 !CBB_flush(&kse_bytes)) {
2396 return false;
2397 }
2398 }
2399
2400 // Save the contents of the extension to repeat it in the second
2401 // ClientHello.
2402 if (ssl->s3 && !ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request &&
2403 !hs->key_share_bytes.CopyFrom(
2404 MakeConstSpan(CBB_data(&kse_bytes), CBB_len(&kse_bytes)))) {
2405 return false;
2406 }
2407
2408 return CBB_flush(out);
2409}

2411bool ssl_ext_key_share_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
2412 Array<uint8_t> *out_secret,
2413 uint8_t *out_alert, CBS *contents) {
2414 CBS peer_key;
2415 uint16_t group_id;
2416 if (!CBS_get_u16(contents, &group_id) ||
2417 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &peer_key) ||
2418 CBS_len(contents) != 0) {
2419 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2420 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2421 return false;
2422 }
2423
2424 SSLKeyShare *key_share = hs->key_shares[0].get();
2425 if (key_share->GroupID() != group_id) {
2426 if (!hs->key_shares[1] || hs->key_shares[1]->GroupID() != group_id) {
2427 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
2428 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_CURVE);
2429 return false;
2430 }
2431 key_share = hs->key_shares[1].get();
2432 }
2433
2434 if (!key_share->Finish(out_secret, out_alert, peer_key)) {
2435 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
2436 return false;
2437 }
2438
2439 hs->new_session->group_id = group_id;
2440 hs->key_shares[0].reset();
2441 hs->key_shares[1].reset();
2442 return true;
2443}

2445bool ssl_ext_key_share_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, bool *out_found,
2446 Span<const uint8_t> *out_peer_key,
2447 uint8_t *out_alert,
2448 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
2449 // We only support connections that include an ECDHE key exchange.
2450 CBS contents;
2451 if (!ssl_client_hello_get_extension(client_hello, &contents,
2452 TLSEXT_TYPE_key_share)) {
2453 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_MISSING_KEY_SHARE);
2454 *out_alert = SSL_AD_MISSING_EXTENSION;
2455 return false;
2456 }
2457
2458 CBS key_shares;
2459 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &key_shares) ||
2460 CBS_len(&contents) != 0) {
2461 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2462 return false;
2463 }
2464
2465 // Find the corresponding key share.
2466 const uint16_t group_id = hs->new_session->group_id;
2467 CBS peer_key;
2468 CBS_init(&peer_key, nullptr, 0);
2469 while (CBS_len(&key_shares) > 0) {
2470 uint16_t id;
2471 CBS peer_key_tmp;
2472 if (!CBS_get_u16(&key_shares, &id) ||
2473 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&key_shares, &peer_key_tmp) ||
2474 CBS_len(&peer_key_tmp) == 0) {
2475 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2476 return false;
2477 }
2478
2479 if (id == group_id) {
2480 if (CBS_len(&peer_key) != 0) {
2481 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DUPLICATE_KEY_SHARE);
2482 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
2483 return false;
2484 }
2485
2486 peer_key = peer_key_tmp;
2487 // Continue parsing the structure to keep peers honest.
2488 }
2489 }
2490
2491 if (out_peer_key != nullptr) {
2492 *out_peer_key = peer_key;
2493 }
2494 *out_found = CBS_len(&peer_key) != 0;
2495 return true;
2496}

2498bool ssl_ext_key_share_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
2499 CBB kse_bytes, public_key;
2500 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_key_share) ||
2501 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &kse_bytes) ||
2502 !CBB_add_u16(&kse_bytes, hs->new_session->group_id) ||
2503 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&kse_bytes, &public_key) ||
2504 !CBB_add_bytes(&public_key, hs->ecdh_public_key.data(),
2505 hs->ecdh_public_key.size()) ||
2506 !CBB_flush(out)) {
2507 return false;
2508 }
2509 return true;
2510}

2545// Cookie
2546//
2547// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8446#section-4.2.2

2549static bool ext_cookie_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {

2553
2554 CBB contents, cookie;
2555 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_cookie) ||
2556 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
2557 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &cookie) ||
2558 !CBB_add_bytes(&cookie, hs->cookie.data(), hs->cookie.size()) ||
2559 !CBB_flush(out)) {
2560 return false;
2561 }
2562
2563 // The cookie is no longer needed in memory.
2564 hs->cookie.Reset();
2565 return true;
2566}

2569// Supported Groups
2570//
2571// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4492#section-5.1.1
2572// https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8446#section-4.2.7
2573
2574static bool ext_supported_groups_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
2575 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2576 CBB contents, groups_bytes;
2577 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_groups) ||
2578 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
2579 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &groups_bytes)) {
2580 return false;
2581 }
2582
2583 // Add a fake group. See draft-davidben-tls-grease-01.
2584 if (ssl->ctx->grease_enabled &&
2585 !CBB_add_u16(&groups_bytes,
2586 ssl_get_grease_value(hs, ssl_grease_group))) {
2587 return false;
2588 }
2589
2590 for (uint16_t group : tls1_get_grouplist(hs)) {
2591 if (is_post_quantum_group(group) &&
2592 hs->max_version < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
2593 continue;
2594 }
2595 if (!CBB_add_u16(&groups_bytes, group)) {
2596 return false;
2597 }
2598 }
2599
2600 return CBB_flush(out);
2601}

2605 CBS *contents) {
2606 // This extension is not expected to be echoed by servers in TLS 1.2, but some
2607 // BigIP servers send it nonetheless, so do not enforce this.
2608 return true;
2609}
2610
2611static bool parse_u16_array(const CBS *cbs, Array<uint16_t> *out) {
2612 CBS copy = *cbs;
2613 if ((CBS_len(&copy) & 1) != 0) {
2614 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
2615 return false;
2616 }
2617
2618 Array<uint16_t> ret;
2619 if (!ret.Init(CBS_len(&copy) / 2)) {
2620 return false;
2621 }
2622 for (size_t i = 0; i < ret.size(); i++) {
2623 if (!CBS_get_u16(&copy, &ret[i])) {
2624 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
2625 return false;
2626 }
2627 }
2628
2629 assert(CBS_len(&copy) == 0);
2630 *out = std::move(ret);
2631 return 1;
2632}

2634static bool ext_supported_groups_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
2635 uint8_t *out_alert,
2636 CBS *contents) {
2637 if (contents == NULL) {
2638 return true;
2639 }
2640
2641 CBS supported_group_list;
2642 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(contents, &supported_group_list) ||
2643 CBS_len(&supported_group_list) == 0 ||
2644 CBS_len(contents) != 0 ||
2645 !parse_u16_array(&supported_group_list, &hs->peer_supported_group_list)) {
2646 return false;
2647 }
2648
2649 return true;
2650}

2652// Token Binding
2653//
2654// https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-tokbind-negotiation-10
2655
2656// The Token Binding version number currently matches the draft number of
2657// draft-ietf-tokbind-protocol, and when published as an RFC it will be 0x0100.
2658// Since there are no wire changes to the protocol from draft 13 through the
2659// current draft (16), this implementation supports all versions in that range.
2660static uint16_t kTokenBindingMaxVersion = 16;
2661static uint16_t kTokenBindingMinVersion = 13;
2662
2663static bool ext_token_binding_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
2664 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2665 if (hs->config->token_binding_params.empty() || SSL_is_dtls(ssl)) {
2666 return true;
2667 }
2668
2669 CBB contents, params;
2670 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_token_binding) ||
2671 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
2672 !CBB_add_u16(&contents, kTokenBindingMaxVersion) ||
2673 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&contents, &params) ||
2674 !CBB_add_bytes(&params, hs->config->token_binding_params.data(),
2675 hs->config->token_binding_params.size()) ||
2676 !CBB_flush(out)) {
2677 return false;
2678 }
2679
2680 return true;
2681}
2682
2683static bool ext_token_binding_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
2684 uint8_t *out_alert,
2685 CBS *contents) {
2686 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2687 if (contents == nullptr) {
2688 return true;
2689 }
2690
2691 CBS params_list;
2692 uint16_t version;
2693 uint8_t param;
2694 if (!CBS_get_u16(contents, &version) ||
2695 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &params_list) ||
2696 !CBS_get_u8(&params_list, &param) ||
2697 CBS_len(&params_list) > 0 ||
2698 CBS_len(contents) > 0) {
2699 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2700 return false;
2701 }
2702
2703 // The server-negotiated version must be less than or equal to our version.
2704 if (version > kTokenBindingMaxVersion) {
2705 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
2706 return false;
2707 }
2708
2709 // If the server-selected version is less than what we support, then Token
2710 // Binding wasn't negotiated (but the extension was parsed successfully).
2711 if (version < kTokenBindingMinVersion) {
2712 return true;
2713 }
2714
2715 for (uint8_t config_param : hs->config->token_binding_params) {
2716 if (param == config_param) {
2717 ssl->s3->negotiated_token_binding_param = param;
2718 ssl->s3->token_binding_negotiated = true;
2719 return true;
2720 }
2721 }
2722
2723 *out_alert = SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER;
2724 return false;
2725}
2726
2727// select_tb_param looks for the first token binding param in
2728// |hs->ssl->token_binding_params| that is also in |params| and puts it in
2729// |hs->ssl->negotiated_token_binding_param|. It returns true if a token binding
2730// param is found, and false otherwise.
2731static bool select_tb_param(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
2732 Span<const uint8_t> peer_params) {
2733 for (uint8_t tb_param : hs->config->token_binding_params) {
2734 for (uint8_t peer_param : peer_params) {
2735 if (tb_param == peer_param) {
2736 hs->ssl->s3->negotiated_token_binding_param = tb_param;
2737 return true;
2738 }
2739 }
2740 }
2741 return false;
2742}
2743
2744static bool ext_token_binding_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
2745 uint8_t *out_alert,
2746 CBS *contents) {
2747 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2748 if (contents == nullptr || hs->config->token_binding_params.empty()) {
2749 return true;
2750 }
2751
2752 CBS params;
2753 uint16_t version;
2754 if (!CBS_get_u16(contents, &version) ||
2755 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &params) ||
2756 CBS_len(&params) == 0 ||
2757 CBS_len(contents) > 0) {
2758 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
2759 return false;
2760 }
2761
2762 // If the client-selected version is less than what we support, then Token
2763 // Binding wasn't negotiated (but the extension was parsed successfully).
2764 if (version < kTokenBindingMinVersion) {
2765 return true;
2766 }
2767
2768 // If the client-selected version is higher than we support, use our max
2769 // version. Otherwise, use the client's version.
2770 hs->negotiated_token_binding_version =
2771 std::min(version, kTokenBindingMaxVersion);
2772 if (!select_tb_param(hs, params)) {
2773 return true;
2774 }
2775
2776 ssl->s3->token_binding_negotiated = true;
2777 return true;
2778}
2779
2780static bool ext_token_binding_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
2781 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2782
2783 if (!ssl->s3->token_binding_negotiated) {
2784 return true;
2785 }
2786
2787 CBB contents, params;
2788 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_token_binding) ||
2789 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
2790 !CBB_add_u16(&contents, hs->negotiated_token_binding_version) ||
2791 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&contents, &params) ||
2792 !CBB_add_u8(&params, ssl->s3->negotiated_token_binding_param) ||
2793 !CBB_flush(out)) {
2794 return false;
2795 }
2796
2797 return true;
2798}

2884static bool ext_quic_transport_params_parse_clienthello_impl(
2885 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert, CBS *contents,
2886 bool used_legacy_codepoint) {
2887 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
2888 if (!contents) {
2889 if (!ssl->quic_method) {
2890 if (hs->config->quic_transport_params.empty()) {
2891 return true;

2901 return true;

2904 return false;
2905 }
2906 if (!ssl->quic_method) {
2907 if (used_legacy_codepoint) {

2909 // to mean something else than QUIC transport parameters.

2913 // because that is not allowed outside of QUIC.

2915 return false;

2919 // Silently ignore because we expect the other QUIC codepoint.
2920 return true;

2923}

3017// Certificate compression
3018
3019static bool cert_compression_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
3020 bool first = true;
3021 CBB contents, algs;
3022
3023 for (const auto &alg : hs->ssl->ctx->cert_compression_algs) {
3024 if (alg.decompress == nullptr) {
3025 continue;
3026 }
3027
3028 if (first && (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_cert_compression) ||
3029 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
3030 !CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&contents, &algs))) {
3031 return false;
3032 }
3033 first = false;
3034 if (!CBB_add_u16(&algs, alg.alg_id)) {
3035 return false;
3036 }
3037 }
3038
3039 return first || CBB_flush(out);
3040}
3041
3042static bool cert_compression_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
3043 uint8_t *out_alert,
3044 CBS *contents) {
3045 if (contents == nullptr) {
3046 return true;
3047 }
3048
3049 // The server may not echo this extension. Any server to client negotiation is
3050 // advertised in the CertificateRequest message.
3051 return false;
3052}
3053
3054static bool cert_compression_parse_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
3055 uint8_t *out_alert,
3056 CBS *contents) {
3057 if (contents == nullptr) {
3058 return true;
3059 }
3060
3061 const SSL_CTX *ctx = hs->ssl->ctx.get();
3062 const size_t num_algs = ctx->cert_compression_algs.size();
3063
3064 CBS alg_ids;
3065 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(contents, &alg_ids) ||
3066 CBS_len(contents) != 0 ||
3067 CBS_len(&alg_ids) == 0 ||
3068 CBS_len(&alg_ids) % 2 == 1) {
3069 return false;
3070 }
3071
3072 const size_t num_given_alg_ids = CBS_len(&alg_ids) / 2;
3073 Array<uint16_t> given_alg_ids;
3074 if (!given_alg_ids.Init(num_given_alg_ids)) {
3075 return false;
3076 }
3077
3078 size_t best_index = num_algs;
3079 size_t given_alg_idx = 0;
3080
3081 while (CBS_len(&alg_ids) > 0) {
3082 uint16_t alg_id;
3083 if (!CBS_get_u16(&alg_ids, &alg_id)) {
3084 return false;
3085 }
3086
3087 given_alg_ids[given_alg_idx++] = alg_id;
3088
3089 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_algs; i++) {
3090 const auto &alg = ctx->cert_compression_algs[i];
3091 if (alg.alg_id == alg_id && alg.compress != nullptr) {
3092 if (i < best_index) {
3093 best_index = i;
3094 }
3095 break;
3096 }
3097 }
3098 }
3099
3100 qsort(given_alg_ids.data(), given_alg_ids.size(), sizeof(uint16_t),
3101 compare_uint16_t);
3102 for (size_t i = 1; i < num_given_alg_ids; i++) {
3103 if (given_alg_ids[i - 1] == given_alg_ids[i]) {
3104 return false;
3105 }
3106 }
3107
3108 if (best_index < num_algs &&
3109 ssl_protocol_version(hs->ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
3110 hs->cert_compression_negotiated = true;
3111 hs->cert_compression_alg_id = ctx->cert_compression_algs[best_index].alg_id;
3112 }
3113
3114 return true;
3115}

3118 return true;
3119}

3121// Application-level Protocol Settings
3122//
3123// https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-vvv-tls-alps-01
3124
3125static bool ext_alps_add_clienthello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
3126 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3127 if (// ALPS requires TLS 1.3.
3128 hs->max_version < TLS1_3_VERSION ||
3129 // Do not offer ALPS without ALPN.
3130 hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.empty() ||
3131 // Do not offer ALPS if not configured.
3132 hs->config->alps_configs.empty() ||
3133 // Do not offer ALPS on renegotiation handshakes.
3134 ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete) {
3135 return true;
3136 }
3137
3138 CBB contents, proto_list, proto;
3139 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_application_settings) ||
3140 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
3141 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&contents, &proto_list)) {
3142 return false;
3143 }
3144
3145 for (const ALPSConfig &config : hs->config->alps_configs) {
3146 if (!CBB_add_u8_length_prefixed(&proto_list, &proto) ||
3147 !CBB_add_bytes(&proto, config.protocol.data(),
3148 config.protocol.size())) {
3149 return false;
3150 }
3151 }
3152
3153 return CBB_flush(out);
3154}
3155
3156static bool ext_alps_parse_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
3157 CBS *contents) {
3158 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3159 if (contents == nullptr) {
3160 return true;
3161 }
3162
3163 assert(!ssl->s3->initial_handshake_complete);
3164 assert(!hs->config->alpn_client_proto_list.empty());
3165 assert(!hs->config->alps_configs.empty());
3166
3167 // ALPS requires TLS 1.3.
3168 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
3169 *out_alert = SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION;
3170 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
3171 return false;
3172 }
3173
3174 // Note extension callbacks may run in any order, so we defer checking
3175 // consistency with ALPN to |ssl_check_serverhello_tlsext|.
3176 if (!hs->new_session->peer_application_settings.CopyFrom(*contents)) {
3177 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
3178 return false;
3179 }
3180
3181 hs->new_session->has_application_settings = true;
3182 return true;
3183}
3184
3185static bool ext_alps_add_serverhello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
3186 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3187 // If early data is accepted, we omit the ALPS extension. It is implicitly
3188 // carried over from the previous connection.
3189 if (hs->new_session == nullptr ||
3190 !hs->new_session->has_application_settings ||
3191 ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
3192 return true;
3193 }
3194
3195 CBB contents;
3196 if (!CBB_add_u16(out, TLSEXT_TYPE_application_settings) ||
3197 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &contents) ||
3198 !CBB_add_bytes(&contents,
3199 hs->new_session->local_application_settings.data(),
3200 hs->new_session->local_application_settings.size()) ||
3201 !CBB_flush(out)) {
3202 return false;
3203 }
3204
3205 return true;
3206}
3207
3208bool ssl_negotiate_alps(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out_alert,
3209 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
3210 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3211 if (ssl->s3->alpn_selected.empty()) {
3212 return true;
3213 }
3214
3215 // If we negotiate ALPN over TLS 1.3, try to negotiate ALPS.
3216 CBS alps_contents;
3217 Span<const uint8_t> settings;
3218 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION &&
3219 ssl_get_local_application_settings(hs, &settings,
3220 ssl->s3->alpn_selected) &&
3221 ssl_client_hello_get_extension(client_hello, &alps_contents,
3222 TLSEXT_TYPE_application_settings)) {
3223 // Check if the client supports ALPS with the selected ALPN.
3224 bool found = false;
3225 CBS alps_list;
3226 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&alps_contents, &alps_list) ||
3227 CBS_len(&alps_contents) != 0 ||
3228 CBS_len(&alps_list) == 0) {
3229 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
3230 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3231 return false;
3232 }
3233 while (CBS_len(&alps_list) > 0) {
3234 CBS protocol_name;
3235 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&alps_list, &protocol_name) ||
3236 // Empty protocol names are forbidden.
3237 CBS_len(&protocol_name) == 0) {
3238 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
3239 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3240 return false;
3241 }
3242 if (protocol_name == MakeConstSpan(ssl->s3->alpn_selected)) {
3243 found = true;
3244 }
3245 }
3246
3247 // Negotiate ALPS if both client also supports ALPS for this protocol.
3248 if (found) {
3249 hs->new_session->has_application_settings = true;
3250 if (!hs->new_session->local_application_settings.CopyFrom(settings)) {
3251 *out_alert = SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR;
3252 return false;
3253 }
3254 }
3255 }
3256
3257 return true;
3258}
