3475#define kNumExtensions (sizeof(kExtensions) / sizeof(struct tls_extension))
3476
3477static_assert(kNumExtensions <=
3478 sizeof(((SSL_HANDSHAKE *)NULL)->extensions.sent) * 8,
3479 "too many extensions for sent bitset");
3480static_assert(kNumExtensions <=
3481 sizeof(((SSL_HANDSHAKE *)NULL)->extensions.received) * 8,
3482 "too many extensions for received bitset");
3483
3484static const struct tls_extension *tls_extension_find(uint32_t *out_index,
3485 uint16_t value) {
3486 unsigned i;
3487 for (i = 0; i < kNumExtensions; i++) {
3488 if (kExtensions[i].value == value) {
3489 *out_index = i;
3490 return &kExtensions[i];
3491 }
3492 }
3493
3494 return NULL;
3495}
3496
3497bool ssl_add_clienthello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out,
3498 size_t header_len) {
3499 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3500 CBB extensions;
3501 if (!CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &extensions)) {
3502 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
3503 return false;
3504 }
3505
3506 // Note we may send multiple ClientHellos for DTLS HelloVerifyRequest and TLS
3507 // 1.3 HelloRetryRequest. For the latter, the extensions may change, so it is
3508 // important to reset this value.
3509 hs->extensions.sent = 0;
3510
3511 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumExtensions; i++) {
3512 if (kExtensions[i].init != NULL) {
3513 kExtensions[i].init(hs);
3514 }
3515 }
3516
3517 uint16_t grease_ext1 = 0;
3518 if (ssl->ctx->grease_enabled) {
3519 // Add a fake empty extension. See draft-davidben-tls-grease-01.
3520 grease_ext1 = ssl_get_grease_value(hs, ssl_grease_extension1);
3521 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions, grease_ext1) ||
3522 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, 0 /* zero length */)) {
3523 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
3524 return false;
3525 }
3526 }
3527
3528 bool last_was_empty = false;
3529 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumExtensions; i++) {
3530 const size_t len_before = CBB_len(&extensions);
3531 if (!kExtensions[i].add_clienthello(hs, &extensions)) {
3532 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ERROR_ADDING_EXTENSION);
3533 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension %u", (unsigned)kExtensions[i].value);
3534 return false;
3535 }
3536
3537 const size_t bytes_written = CBB_len(&extensions) - len_before;
3538 if (bytes_written != 0) {
3539 hs->extensions.sent |= (1u << i);
3540 }
3541 // If the difference in lengths is only four bytes then the extension had
3542 // an empty body.
3543 last_was_empty = (bytes_written == 4);
3544 }
3545
3546 if (ssl->ctx->grease_enabled) {
3547 // Add a fake non-empty extension. See draft-davidben-tls-grease-01.
3548 uint16_t grease_ext2 = ssl_get_grease_value(hs, ssl_grease_extension2);
3549
3550 // The two fake extensions must not have the same value. GREASE values are
3551 // of the form 0x1a1a, 0x2a2a, 0x3a3a, etc., so XOR to generate a different
3552 // one.
3553 if (grease_ext1 == grease_ext2) {
3554 grease_ext2 ^= 0x1010;
3555 }
3556
3557 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions, grease_ext2) ||
3558 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, 1 /* one byte length */) ||
3559 !CBB_add_u8(&extensions, 0 /* single zero byte as contents */)) {
3560 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
3561 return false;
3562 }
3563
3564 last_was_empty = false;
3565 }
3566
3567 if (!SSL_is_dtls(ssl) && !ssl->quic_method) {
3568 size_t psk_extension_len = ext_pre_shared_key_clienthello_length(hs);
3569 header_len += 2 + CBB_len(&extensions) + psk_extension_len;
3570 size_t padding_len = 0;
3571
3572 // The final extension must be non-empty. WebSphere Application
3573 // Server 7.0 is intolerant to the last extension being zero-length. See
3574 // https://crbug.com/363583.
3575 if (last_was_empty && psk_extension_len == 0) {
3576 padding_len = 1;
3577 // The addition of the padding extension may push us into the F5 bug.
3578 header_len += 4 + padding_len;
3579 }
3580
3581 // Add padding to workaround bugs in F5 terminators. See RFC 7685.
3582 //
3583 // NB: because this code works out the length of all existing extensions
3584 // it MUST always appear last (save for any PSK extension).
3585 if (header_len > 0xff && header_len < 0x200) {
3586 // If our calculations already included a padding extension, remove that
3587 // factor because we're about to change its length.
3588 if (padding_len != 0) {
3589 header_len -= 4 + padding_len;
3590 }
3591 padding_len = 0x200 - header_len;
3592 // Extensions take at least four bytes to encode. Always include at least
3593 // one byte of data if including the extension. WebSphere Application
3594 // Server 7.0 is intolerant to the last extension being zero-length. See
3595 // https://crbug.com/363583.
3596 if (padding_len >= 4 + 1) {
3597 padding_len -= 4;
3598 } else {
3599 padding_len = 1;
3600 }
3601 }
3602
3603 if (padding_len != 0) {
3604 uint8_t *padding_bytes;
3605 if (!CBB_add_u16(&extensions, TLSEXT_TYPE_padding) ||
3606 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, padding_len) ||
3607 !CBB_add_space(&extensions, &padding_bytes, padding_len)) {
3608 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
3609 return false;
3610 }
3611
3612 OPENSSL_memset(padding_bytes, 0, padding_len);
3613 }
3614 }
3615
3616 // The PSK extension must be last, including after the padding.
3617 if (!ext_pre_shared_key_add_clienthello(hs, &extensions)) {
3618 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
3619 return false;
3620 }
3621
3622 // Discard empty extensions blocks.
3623 if (CBB_len(&extensions) == 0) {
3624 CBB_discard_child(out);
3625 }
3626
3627 return CBB_flush(out);
3628}
3629
3630bool ssl_add_serverhello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *out) {
3631 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3632 CBB extensions;
3633 if (!CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(out, &extensions)) {
3634 goto err;
3635 }
3636
3637 for (unsigned i = 0; i < kNumExtensions; i++) {
3638 if (!(hs->extensions.received & (1u << i))) {
3639 // Don't send extensions that were not received.
3640 continue;
3641 }
3642
3643 if (!kExtensions[i].add_serverhello(hs, &extensions)) {
3644 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ERROR_ADDING_EXTENSION);
3645 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension %u", (unsigned)kExtensions[i].value);
3646 goto err;
3647 }
3648 }
3649
3650 // Discard empty extensions blocks before TLS 1.3.
3651 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) < TLS1_3_VERSION &&
3652 CBB_len(&extensions) == 0) {
3653 CBB_discard_child(out);
3654 }
3655
3656 return CBB_flush(out);
3657
3658err:
3659 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
3660 return false;
3661}
3662
3663static bool ssl_scan_clienthello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
3664 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello,
3665 int *out_alert) {
3666 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumExtensions; i++) {
3667 if (kExtensions[i].init != NULL) {
3668 kExtensions[i].init(hs);
3669 }
3670 }
3671
3672 hs->extensions.received = 0;
3673 CBS extensions;
3674 CBS_init(&extensions, client_hello->extensions, client_hello->extensions_len);
3675 while (CBS_len(&extensions) != 0) {
3676 uint16_t type;
3677 CBS extension;
3678
3679 // Decode the next extension.
3680 if (!CBS_get_u16(&extensions, &type) ||
3681 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &extension)) {
3682 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3683 return false;
3684 }
3685
3686 unsigned ext_index;
3687 const struct tls_extension *const ext =
3688 tls_extension_find(&ext_index, type);
3689 if (ext == NULL) {
3690 continue;
3691 }
3692
3693 hs->extensions.received |= (1u << ext_index);
3694 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3695 if (!ext->parse_clienthello(hs, &alert, &extension)) {
3696 *out_alert = alert;
3697 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ERROR_PARSING_EXTENSION);
3698 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension %u", (unsigned)type);
3699 return false;
3700 }
3701 }
3702
3703 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumExtensions; i++) {
3704 if (hs->extensions.received & (1u << i)) {
3705 continue;
3706 }
3707
3708 CBS *contents = NULL, fake_contents;
3709 static const uint8_t kFakeRenegotiateExtension[] = {0};
3710 if (kExtensions[i].value == TLSEXT_TYPE_renegotiate &&
3711 ssl_client_cipher_list_contains_cipher(client_hello,
3712 SSL3_CK_SCSV & 0xffff)) {
3713 // The renegotiation SCSV was received so pretend that we received a
3714 // renegotiation extension.
3715 CBS_init(&fake_contents, kFakeRenegotiateExtension,
3716 sizeof(kFakeRenegotiateExtension));
3717 contents = &fake_contents;
3718 hs->extensions.received |= (1u << i);
3719 }
3720
3721 // Extension wasn't observed so call the callback with a NULL
3722 // parameter.
3723 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3724 if (!kExtensions[i].parse_clienthello(hs, &alert, contents)) {
3725 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_MISSING_EXTENSION);
3726 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension %u", (unsigned)kExtensions[i].value);
3727 *out_alert = alert;
3728 return false;
3729 }
3730 }
3731
3732 return true;
3733}
3734
3735bool ssl_parse_clienthello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs,
3736 const SSL_CLIENT_HELLO *client_hello) {
3737 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3738 int alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3739 if (!ssl_scan_clienthello_tlsext(hs, client_hello, &alert)) {
3740 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
3741 return false;
3742 }
3743
3744 if (!ssl_check_clienthello_tlsext(hs)) {
3745 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CLIENTHELLO_TLSEXT);
3746 return false;
3747 }
3748
3749 return true;
3750}
3751
3752static bool ssl_scan_serverhello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBS *cbs,
3753 int *out_alert) {
3754 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3755 // Before TLS 1.3, ServerHello extensions blocks may be omitted if empty.
3756 if (CBS_len(cbs) == 0 && ssl_protocol_version(ssl) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
3757 return true;
3758 }
3759
3760 // Decode the extensions block and check it is valid.
3761 CBS extensions;
3762 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(cbs, &extensions) ||
3763 !tls1_check_duplicate_extensions(&extensions)) {
3764 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3765 return false;
3766 }
3767
3768 uint32_t received = 0;
3769 while (CBS_len(&extensions) != 0) {
3770 uint16_t type;
3771 CBS extension;
3772
3773 // Decode the next extension.
3774 if (!CBS_get_u16(&extensions, &type) ||
3775 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &extension)) {
3776 *out_alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3777 return false;
3778 }
3779
3780 unsigned ext_index;
3781 const struct tls_extension *const ext =
3782 tls_extension_find(&ext_index, type);
3783
3784 if (ext == NULL) {
3785 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
3786 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension %u", (unsigned)type);
3787 *out_alert = SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION;
3788 return false;
3789 }
3790
3791 static_assert(kNumExtensions <= sizeof(hs->extensions.sent) * 8,
3792 "too many bits");
3793
3794 if (!(hs->extensions.sent & (1u << ext_index))) {
3795 // If the extension was never sent then it is illegal.
3796 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
3797 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension :%u", (unsigned)type);
3798 *out_alert = SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION;
3799 return false;
3800 }
3801
3802 received |= (1u << ext_index);
3803
3804 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3805 if (!ext->parse_serverhello(hs, &alert, &extension)) {
3806 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ERROR_PARSING_EXTENSION);
3807 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension %u", (unsigned)type);
3808 *out_alert = alert;
3809 return false;
3810 }
3811 }
3812
3813 for (size_t i = 0; i < kNumExtensions; i++) {
3814 if (!(received & (1u << i))) {
3815 // Extension wasn't observed so call the callback with a NULL
3816 // parameter.
3817 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3818 if (!kExtensions[i].parse_serverhello(hs, &alert, NULL)) {
3819 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_MISSING_EXTENSION);
3820 ERR_add_error_dataf("extension %u", (unsigned)kExtensions[i].value);
3821 *out_alert = alert;
3822 return false;
3823 }
3824 }
3825 }
3826
3827 return true;
3828}
3829
3830static bool ssl_check_clienthello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
3831 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3832
3833 if (ssl->s3->token_binding_negotiated &&
3834 !(SSL_get_secure_renegotiation_support(ssl) &&
3835 SSL_get_extms_support(ssl))) {
3836 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NEGOTIATED_TB_WITHOUT_EMS_OR_RI);
3837 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION);
3838 return false;
3839 }
3840
3841 int ret = SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_NOACK;
3842 int al = SSL_AD_UNRECOGNIZED_NAME;
3843
3844 if (ssl->ctx->servername_callback != 0) {
3845 ret = ssl->ctx->servername_callback(ssl, &al, ssl->ctx->servername_arg);
3846 } else if (ssl->session_ctx->servername_callback != 0) {
3847 ret = ssl->session_ctx->servername_callback(
3848 ssl, &al, ssl->session_ctx->servername_arg);
3849 }
3850
3851 switch (ret) {
3852 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_ALERT_FATAL:
3853 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, al);
3854 return false;
3855
3856 case SSL_TLSEXT_ERR_NOACK:
3857 hs->should_ack_sni = false;
3858 return true;
3859
3860 default:
3861 return true;
3862 }
3863}
3864
3865static bool ssl_check_serverhello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
3866 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3867 // ALPS and ALPN have a dependency between each other, so we defer checking
3868 // consistency to after the callbacks run.
3869 if (hs->new_session != nullptr && hs->new_session->has_application_settings) {
3870 // ALPN must be negotiated.
3871 if (ssl->s3->alpn_selected.empty()) {
3872 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NEGOTIATED_ALPS_WITHOUT_ALPN);
3873 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
3874 return false;
3875 }
3876
3877 // The negotiated protocol must be one of the ones we advertised for ALPS.
3878 Span<const uint8_t> settings;
3879 if (!ssl_get_local_application_settings(hs, &settings,
3880 ssl->s3->alpn_selected)) {
3881 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_INVALID_ALPN_PROTOCOL);
3882 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
3883 return false;
3884 }
3885
3886 if (!hs->new_session->local_application_settings.CopyFrom(settings)) {
3887 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
3888 return false;
3889 }
3890 }
3891
3892 return true;
3893}

3895bool ssl_parse_serverhello_tlsext(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBS *cbs) {
3896 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
3897 int alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
3898 if (!ssl_scan_serverhello_tlsext(hs, cbs, &alert)) {
3899 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
3900 return false;
3901 }
3902
3903 if (!ssl_check_serverhello_tlsext(hs)) {
3904 return false;
3905 }
3906
3907 return true;

3910static enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t decrypt_ticket_with_cipher_ctx(
3911 Array<uint8_t> *out, EVP_CIPHER_CTX *cipher_ctx, HMAC_CTX *hmac_ctx,
3912 Span<const uint8_t> ticket) {
3913 size_t iv_len = EVP_CIPHER_CTX_iv_length(cipher_ctx);
3914
3915 // Check the MAC at the end of the ticket.
3916 uint8_t mac[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
3917 size_t mac_len = HMAC_size(hmac_ctx);
3918 if (ticket.size() < SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN + iv_len + 1 + mac_len) {
3919 // The ticket must be large enough for key name, IV, data, and MAC.
3920 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
3921 }
3922 // Split the ticket into the ticket and the MAC.
3923 auto ticket_mac = ticket.subspan(ticket.size() - mac_len);
3924 ticket = ticket.subspan(0, ticket.size() - mac_len);
3925 HMAC_Update(hmac_ctx, ticket.data(), ticket.size());
3926 HMAC_Final(hmac_ctx, mac, NULL);
3927 assert(mac_len == ticket_mac.size());
3928 bool mac_ok = CRYPTO_memcmp(mac, ticket_mac.data(), mac_len) == 0;
3929#if defined(BORINGSSL_UNSAFE_FUZZER_MODE)
3930 mac_ok = true;
3931#endif
3932 if (!mac_ok) {
3933 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
3934 }
3935
3936 // Decrypt the session data.
3937 auto ciphertext = ticket.subspan(SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN + iv_len);
3938 Array<uint8_t> plaintext;
3939#if defined(BORINGSSL_UNSAFE_FUZZER_MODE)
3940 if (!plaintext.CopyFrom(ciphertext)) {
3941 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
3942 }
3943#else
3944 if (ciphertext.size() >= INT_MAX) {
3945 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
3946 }
3947 if (!plaintext.Init(ciphertext.size())) {
3948 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
3949 }
3950 int len1, len2;
3951 if (!EVP_DecryptUpdate(cipher_ctx, plaintext.data(), &len1, ciphertext.data(),
3952 (int)ciphertext.size()) ||
3953 !EVP_DecryptFinal_ex(cipher_ctx, plaintext.data() + len1, &len2)) {
3954 ERR_clear_error();
3955 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
3956 }
3957 plaintext.Shrink(static_cast<size_t>(len1) + len2);
3958#endif
3959
3960 *out = std::move(plaintext);
3961 return ssl_ticket_aead_success;
3962}
3963
3964static enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t ssl_decrypt_ticket_with_cb(
3965 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, Array<uint8_t> *out, bool *out_renew_ticket,
3966 Span<const uint8_t> ticket) {
3967 assert(ticket.size() >= SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN + EVP_MAX_IV_LENGTH);
3968 ScopedEVP_CIPHER_CTX cipher_ctx;
3969 ScopedHMAC_CTX hmac_ctx;
3970 auto name = ticket.subspan(0, SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN);
3971 // The actual IV is shorter, but the length is determined by the callback's
3972 // chosen cipher. Instead we pass in |EVP_MAX_IV_LENGTH| worth of IV to ensure
3973 // the callback has enough.
3974 auto iv = ticket.subspan(SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN, EVP_MAX_IV_LENGTH);
3975 int cb_ret = hs->ssl->session_ctx->ticket_key_cb(
3976 hs->ssl, const_cast<uint8_t *>(name.data()),
3977 const_cast<uint8_t *>(iv.data()), cipher_ctx.get(), hmac_ctx.get(),
3978 0 /* decrypt */);
3979 if (cb_ret < 0) {
3980 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
3981 } else if (cb_ret == 0) {
3982 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
3983 } else if (cb_ret == 2) {
3984 *out_renew_ticket = true;
3985 } else {
3986 assert(cb_ret == 1);
3987 }
3988 return decrypt_ticket_with_cipher_ctx(out, cipher_ctx.get(), hmac_ctx.get(),
3989 ticket);
3990}
3991
3992static enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t ssl_decrypt_ticket_with_ticket_keys(
3993 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, Array<uint8_t> *out, Span<const uint8_t> ticket) {
3994 assert(ticket.size() >= SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN + EVP_MAX_IV_LENGTH);
3995 SSL_CTX *ctx = hs->ssl->session_ctx.get();
3996
3997 // Rotate the ticket key if necessary.
3998 if (!ssl_ctx_rotate_ticket_encryption_key(ctx)) {
3999 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
4000 }
4001
4002 const EVP_CIPHER *cipher = EVP_aes_128_cbc();
4003 auto name = ticket.subspan(0, SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN);
4004 auto iv =
4005 ticket.subspan(SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN, EVP_CIPHER_iv_length(cipher));
4006
4007 // Pick the matching ticket key and decrypt.
4008 ScopedEVP_CIPHER_CTX cipher_ctx;
4009 ScopedHMAC_CTX hmac_ctx;
4010 {
4011 MutexReadLock lock(&ctx->lock);
4012 const TicketKey *key;
4013 if (ctx->ticket_key_current && name == ctx->ticket_key_current->name) {
4014 key = ctx->ticket_key_current.get();
4015 } else if (ctx->ticket_key_prev && name == ctx->ticket_key_prev->name) {
4016 key = ctx->ticket_key_prev.get();
4017 } else {
4018 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
4019 }
4020 if (!HMAC_Init_ex(hmac_ctx.get(), key->hmac_key, sizeof(key->hmac_key),
4021 tlsext_tick_md(), NULL) ||
4022 !EVP_DecryptInit_ex(cipher_ctx.get(), cipher, NULL,
4023 key->aes_key, iv.data())) {
4024 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
4025 }
4026 }
4027 return decrypt_ticket_with_cipher_ctx(out, cipher_ctx.get(), hmac_ctx.get(),
4028 ticket);
4029}
4030
4031static enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t ssl_decrypt_ticket_with_method(
4032 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, Array<uint8_t> *out, bool *out_renew_ticket,
4033 Span<const uint8_t> ticket) {
4034 Array<uint8_t> plaintext;
4035 if (!plaintext.Init(ticket.size())) {
4036 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
4037 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
4038 }
4039
4040 size_t plaintext_len;
4041 const enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t result =
4042 hs->ssl->session_ctx->ticket_aead_method->open(
4043 hs->ssl, plaintext.data(), &plaintext_len, ticket.size(),
4044 ticket.data(), ticket.size());
4045 if (result != ssl_ticket_aead_success) {
4046 return result;
4047 }
4048
4049 plaintext.Shrink(plaintext_len);
4050 *out = std::move(plaintext);
4051 return ssl_ticket_aead_success;
4052}
4053
4054enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t ssl_process_ticket(
4055 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> *out_session,
4056 bool *out_renew_ticket, Span<const uint8_t> ticket,
4057 Span<const uint8_t> session_id) {
4058 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
4059 *out_renew_ticket = false;
4060 out_session->reset();
4061
4062 if ((SSL_get_options(hs->ssl) & SSL_OP_NO_TICKET) ||
4063 session_id.size() > SSL_MAX_SSL_SESSION_ID_LENGTH) {
4064 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
4065 }
4066
4067 // Tickets in TLS 1.3 are tied into pre-shared keys (PSKs), unlike in TLS 1.2
4068 // where that concept doesn't exist. The |decrypted_psk| and |ignore_psk|
4069 // hints only apply to PSKs. We check the version to determine which this is.
4070 const bool is_psk = ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION;
4071
4072 Array<uint8_t> plaintext;
4073 enum ssl_ticket_aead_result_t result;
4074 SSL_HANDSHAKE_HINTS *const hints = hs->hints.get();
4075 if (is_psk && hints && !hs->hints_requested &&
4076 !hints->decrypted_psk.empty()) {
4077 result = plaintext.CopyFrom(hints->decrypted_psk) ? ssl_ticket_aead_success
4078 : ssl_ticket_aead_error;
4079 } else if (is_psk && hints && !hs->hints_requested && hints->ignore_psk) {
4080 result = ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
4081 } else if (ssl->session_ctx->ticket_aead_method != NULL) {
4082 result = ssl_decrypt_ticket_with_method(hs, &plaintext, out_renew_ticket,
4083 ticket);
4084 } else {
4085 // Ensure there is room for the key name and the largest IV |ticket_key_cb|
4086 // may try to consume. The real limit may be lower, but the maximum IV
4087 // length should be well under the minimum size for the session material and
4088 // HMAC.
4089 if (ticket.size() < SSL_TICKET_KEY_NAME_LEN + EVP_MAX_IV_LENGTH) {
4090 result = ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
4091 } else if (ssl->session_ctx->ticket_key_cb != NULL) {
4092 result =
4093 ssl_decrypt_ticket_with_cb(hs, &plaintext, out_renew_ticket, ticket);
4094 } else {
4095 result = ssl_decrypt_ticket_with_ticket_keys(hs, &plaintext, ticket);
4096 }
4097 }
4098
4099 if (is_psk && hints && hs->hints_requested) {
4100 if (result == ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket) {
4101 hints->ignore_psk = true;
4102 } else if (result == ssl_ticket_aead_success &&
4103 !hints->decrypted_psk.CopyFrom(plaintext)) {
4104 return ssl_ticket_aead_error;
4105 }
4106 }
4107
4108 if (result != ssl_ticket_aead_success) {
4109 return result;
4110 }
4111
4112 // Decode the session.
4113 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session(SSL_SESSION_from_bytes(
4114 plaintext.data(), plaintext.size(), ssl->ctx.get()));
4115 if (!session) {
4116 ERR_clear_error(); // Don't leave an error on the queue.
4117 return ssl_ticket_aead_ignore_ticket;
4118 }
4119
4120 // Copy the client's session ID into the new session, to denote the ticket has
4121 // been accepted.
4122 OPENSSL_memcpy(session->session_id, session_id.data(), session_id.size());
4123 session->session_id_length = session_id.size();
4124
4125 *out_session = std::move(session);
4126 return ssl_ticket_aead_success;
4127}

4129bool tls1_parse_peer_sigalgs(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, const CBS *in_sigalgs) {
4130 // Extension ignored for inappropriate versions
4131 if (ssl_protocol_version(hs->ssl) < TLS1_2_VERSION) {
4132 return true;
4133 }
4134
4135 // In all contexts, the signature algorithms list may not be empty. (It may be
4136 // omitted by clients in TLS 1.2, but then the entire extension is omitted.)
4137 return CBS_len(in_sigalgs) != 0 &&
4138 parse_u16_array(in_sigalgs, &hs->peer_sigalgs);
4139}
4140
4141bool tls1_get_legacy_signature_algorithm(uint16_t *out, const EVP_PKEY *pkey) {
4142 switch (EVP_PKEY_id(pkey)) {
4143 case EVP_PKEY_RSA:
4144 *out = SSL_SIGN_RSA_PKCS1_MD5_SHA1;
4145 return true;
4146 case EVP_PKEY_EC:
4147 *out = SSL_SIGN_ECDSA_SHA1;
4148 return true;
4149 default:
4150 return false;
4151 }
4152}
4153
4154bool tls1_choose_signature_algorithm(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint16_t *out) {
4155 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
4156 CERT *cert = hs->config->cert.get();
4157 DC *dc = cert->dc.get();
4158
4159 // Before TLS 1.2, the signature algorithm isn't negotiated as part of the
4160 // handshake.
4161 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) < TLS1_2_VERSION) {
4162 if (!tls1_get_legacy_signature_algorithm(out, hs->local_pubkey.get())) {
4163 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_COMMON_SIGNATURE_ALGORITHMS);
4164 return false;
4165 }
4166 return true;
4167 }
4168
4169 Span<const uint16_t> sigalgs = kSignSignatureAlgorithms;
4170 if (ssl_signing_with_dc(hs)) {
4171 sigalgs = MakeConstSpan(&dc->expected_cert_verify_algorithm, 1);
4172 } else if (!cert->sigalgs.empty()) {
4173 sigalgs = cert->sigalgs;
4174 }
4175
4176 Span<const uint16_t> peer_sigalgs = tls1_get_peer_verify_algorithms(hs);
4177
4178 for (uint16_t sigalg : sigalgs) {
4179 // SSL_SIGN_RSA_PKCS1_MD5_SHA1 is an internal value and should never be
4180 // negotiated.
4181 if (sigalg == SSL_SIGN_RSA_PKCS1_MD5_SHA1 ||
4182 !ssl_private_key_supports_signature_algorithm(hs, sigalg)) {
4183 continue;
4184 }
4185
4186 for (uint16_t peer_sigalg : peer_sigalgs) {
4187 if (sigalg == peer_sigalg) {
4188 *out = sigalg;
4189 return true;
4190 }
4191 }
4192 }
4193
4194 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_COMMON_SIGNATURE_ALGORITHMS);
4195 return false;
4196}
4197
4198Span<const uint16_t> tls1_get_peer_verify_algorithms(const SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
4199 Span<const uint16_t> peer_sigalgs = hs->peer_sigalgs;
4200 if (peer_sigalgs.empty() && ssl_protocol_version(hs->ssl) < TLS1_3_VERSION) {
4201 // If the client didn't specify any signature_algorithms extension then
4202 // we can assume that it supports SHA1. See
4203 // http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5246#section-7.4.1.4.1
4204 static const uint16_t kDefaultPeerAlgorithms[] = {SSL_SIGN_RSA_PKCS1_SHA1,
4205 SSL_SIGN_ECDSA_SHA1};
4206 peer_sigalgs = kDefaultPeerAlgorithms;
4207 }
4208 return peer_sigalgs;
4209}
4210
4211bool tls1_verify_channel_id(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, const SSLMessage &msg) {
4212 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
4213 // A Channel ID handshake message is structured to contain multiple
4214 // extensions, but the only one that can be present is Channel ID.
4215 uint16_t extension_type;
4216 CBS channel_id = msg.body, extension;
4217 if (!CBS_get_u16(&channel_id, &extension_type) ||
4218 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&channel_id, &extension) ||
4219 CBS_len(&channel_id) != 0 ||
4220 extension_type != TLSEXT_TYPE_channel_id ||
4221 CBS_len(&extension) != TLSEXT_CHANNEL_ID_SIZE) {
4222 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
4223 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
4224 return false;
4225 }
4226
4227 UniquePtr<EC_GROUP> p256(EC_GROUP_new_by_curve_name(NID_X9_62_prime256v1));
4228 if (!p256) {
4229 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_NO_P256_SUPPORT);
4230 return false;
4231 }
4232
4233 UniquePtr<ECDSA_SIG> sig(ECDSA_SIG_new());
4234 UniquePtr<BIGNUM> x(BN_new()), y(BN_new());
4235 if (!sig || !x || !y) {
4236 return false;
4237 }
4238
4239 const uint8_t *p = CBS_data(&extension);
4240 if (BN_bin2bn(p + 0, 32, x.get()) == NULL ||
4241 BN_bin2bn(p + 32, 32, y.get()) == NULL ||
4242 BN_bin2bn(p + 64, 32, sig->r) == NULL ||
4243 BN_bin2bn(p + 96, 32, sig->s) == NULL) {
4244 return false;
4245 }
4246
4247 UniquePtr<EC_KEY> key(EC_KEY_new());
4248 UniquePtr<EC_POINT> point(EC_POINT_new(p256.get()));
4249 if (!key || !point ||
4250 !EC_POINT_set_affine_coordinates_GFp(p256.get(), point.get(), x.get(),
4251 y.get(), nullptr) ||
4252 !EC_KEY_set_group(key.get(), p256.get()) ||
4253 !EC_KEY_set_public_key(key.get(), point.get())) {
4254 return false;
4255 }
4256
4257 uint8_t digest[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
4258 size_t digest_len;
4259 if (!tls1_channel_id_hash(hs, digest, &digest_len)) {
4260 return false;
4261 }
4262
4263 bool sig_ok = ECDSA_do_verify(digest, digest_len, sig.get(), key.get());
4264#if defined(BORINGSSL_UNSAFE_FUZZER_MODE)
4265 sig_ok = true;
4266 ERR_clear_error();
4267#endif
4268 if (!sig_ok) {
4269 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CHANNEL_ID_SIGNATURE_INVALID);
4270 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECRYPT_ERROR);
4271 ssl->s3->channel_id_valid = false;
4272 return false;
4273 }
4274
4275 OPENSSL_memcpy(ssl->s3->channel_id, p, 64);
4276 return true;
4277}
4278
4279bool tls1_write_channel_id(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, CBB *cbb) {
4280 uint8_t digest[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
4281 size_t digest_len;
4282 if (!tls1_channel_id_hash(hs, digest, &digest_len)) {
4283 return false;
4284 }
4285
4286 EC_KEY *ec_key = EVP_PKEY_get0_EC_KEY(hs->config->channel_id_private.get());
4287 if (ec_key == nullptr) {
4288 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
4289 return false;
4290 }
4291
4292 UniquePtr<BIGNUM> x(BN_new()), y(BN_new());
4293 if (!x || !y ||
4294 !EC_POINT_get_affine_coordinates_GFp(EC_KEY_get0_group(ec_key),
4295 EC_KEY_get0_public_key(ec_key),
4296 x.get(), y.get(), nullptr)) {
4297 return false;
4298 }
4299
4300 UniquePtr<ECDSA_SIG> sig(ECDSA_do_sign(digest, digest_len, ec_key));
4301 if (!sig) {
4302 return false;
4303 }
4304
4305 CBB child;
4306 if (!CBB_add_u16(cbb, TLSEXT_TYPE_channel_id) ||
4307 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(cbb, &child) ||
4308 !BN_bn2cbb_padded(&child, 32, x.get()) ||
4309 !BN_bn2cbb_padded(&child, 32, y.get()) ||
4310 !BN_bn2cbb_padded(&child, 32, sig->r) ||
4311 !BN_bn2cbb_padded(&child, 32, sig->s) ||
4312 !CBB_flush(cbb)) {
4313 return false;
4314 }
4315
4316 return true;
4317}
4318
4319bool tls1_channel_id_hash(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, uint8_t *out, size_t *out_len) {
4320 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
4321 if (ssl_protocol_version(ssl) >= TLS1_3_VERSION) {
4322 Array<uint8_t> msg;
4323 if (!tls13_get_cert_verify_signature_input(hs, &msg,
4324 ssl_cert_verify_channel_id)) {
4325 return false;
4326 }
4327 SHA256(msg.data(), msg.size(), out);
4328 *out_len = SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH;
4329 return true;
4330 }
4331
4332 SHA256_CTX ctx;
4333
4334 SHA256_Init(&ctx);
4335 static const char kClientIDMagic[] = "TLS Channel ID signature";
4336 SHA256_Update(&ctx, kClientIDMagic, sizeof(kClientIDMagic));
4337
4338 if (ssl->session != NULL) {
4339 static const char kResumptionMagic[] = "Resumption";
4340 SHA256_Update(&ctx, kResumptionMagic, sizeof(kResumptionMagic));
4341 if (ssl->session->original_handshake_hash_len == 0) {
4342 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_INTERNAL_ERROR);
4343 return false;
4344 }
4345 SHA256_Update(&ctx, ssl->session->original_handshake_hash,
4346 ssl->session->original_handshake_hash_len);
4347 }
4348
4349 uint8_t hs_hash[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE];
4350 size_t hs_hash_len;
4351 if (!hs->transcript.GetHash(hs_hash, &hs_hash_len)) {
4352 return false;
4353 }
4354 SHA256_Update(&ctx, hs_hash, (size_t)hs_hash_len);
4355 SHA256_Final(out, &ctx);
4356 *out_len = SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH;
4357 return true;
4358}
4359
4360bool tls1_record_handshake_hashes_for_channel_id(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
4361 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
4362 // This function should never be called for a resumed session because the
4363 // handshake hashes that we wish to record are for the original, full
4364 // handshake.
4365 if (ssl->session != NULL) {
4366 return false;
4367 }
4368
4369 static_assert(
4370 sizeof(hs->new_session->original_handshake_hash) == EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE,
4371 "original_handshake_hash is too small");
4372
4373 size_t digest_len;
4374 if (!hs->transcript.GetHash(hs->new_session->original_handshake_hash,
4375 &digest_len)) {
4376 return false;
4377 }
4378
4379 static_assert(EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE <= 0xff,
4380 "EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE does not fit in uint8_t");
4381 hs->new_session->original_handshake_hash_len = (uint8_t)digest_len;
4382
4383 return true;
4384}
4385
4386bool ssl_do_channel_id_callback(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
4387 if (hs->config->channel_id_private != NULL ||
4388 hs->ssl->ctx->channel_id_cb == NULL) {
4389 return true;
4390 }
4391
4392 EVP_PKEY *key = NULL;
4393 hs->ssl->ctx->channel_id_cb(hs->ssl, &key);
4394 if (key == NULL) {
4395 // The caller should try again later.
4396 return true;
4397 }
4398
4399 UniquePtr<EVP_PKEY> free_key(key);
4400 return SSL_set1_tls_channel_id(hs->ssl, key);
4401}
4402
4403bool ssl_is_sct_list_valid(const CBS *contents) {
4404 // Shallow parse the SCT list for sanity. By the RFC
4405 // (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6962#section-3.3) neither the list nor any
4406 // of the SCTs may be empty.
4407 CBS copy = *contents;
4408 CBS sct_list;
4409 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&copy, &sct_list) ||
4410 CBS_len(&copy) != 0 ||
4411 CBS_len(&sct_list) == 0) {
4412 return false;
4413 }
4414
4415 while (CBS_len(&sct_list) > 0) {
4416 CBS sct;
4417 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&sct_list, &sct) ||
4418 CBS_len(&sct) == 0) {
4419 return false;
4420 }
4421 }
4422
4423 return true;
4424}

4431 uint16_t extension_type,
4432 const uint8_t **out_data,
4433 size_t *out_len) {
4434 CBS cbs;
4435 if (!ssl_client_hello_get_extension(client_hello, &cbs, extension_type)) {
4436 return 0;
4437 }
4438
4439 *out_data = CBS_data(&cbs);
4440 *out_len = CBS_len(&cbs);
4441 return 1;
4442}
